       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': '9941b84d-8117-459c-b6f2-c6308983476c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_font example please',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725874.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd121ffb8-7cad-42db-a7e1-cf381dd53240',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```\\nal_color_cmyk\\nal_color_cmyk_to_rgb\\nal_color_hsl\\nal_color_hsl_to_rgb\\nal_color_hsv\\nal_color_hsv_to_rgb\\nal_color_html\\nal_color_html_to_rgb\\nal_color_rgb_to_html\\nal_color_name\\nal_color_name_to_rgb\\nal_color_rgb_to_cmyk\\nal_color_rgb_to_hsl\\nal_color_rgb_to_hsv\\nal_color_rgb_to_name\\nal_color_rgb_to_xyz\\nal_color_xyz\\nal_color_xyz_to_rgb\\nal_color_rgb_to_xyy\\nal_color_xyy\\nal_color_xyy_to_rgb\\nal_color_rgb_to_lab\\nal_color_lab\\nal_color_lab_to_rgb\\nal_color_rgb_to_lch\\nal_color_lch\\nal_color_lch_to_rgb\\nal_color_distance_ciede2000_lab\\nal_color_rgb_to_yuv\\nal_color_yuv\\nal_color_yuv_to_rgb\\nal_get_allegro_color_version\\nal_is_color_valid\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725809.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '240dbf9c-76fb-412f-a919-3c47537b3571',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'YES please',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725794.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1073de36-2440-4444-8bf5-97f9d2ea234e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Would you like me to list all of the functions related to ALLEGRO_COLOR?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725786.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2a334ac0-8880-477a-91af-626413dba448',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```ALLEGRO_COLOR al_color_cmyk(float c, float m, float y, float k)```\\n\\nReturn an ALLEGRO_COLOR structure from CMYK values (cyan, magenta, yellow, black).',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725610.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fab62603-570d-42bb-bafb-3a3ab9d8bd0c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure thing!\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)```\\n\\nLoads a font from disk. This will use al_load_bitmap_font_flags if you pass the name of a known bitmap format, or else al_load_ttf_font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter is passed through to either of those functions. Bitmap and TTF fonts are also affected by the current bitmap flags at the time the font is loaded.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725587.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '934cbfa4-41b7-4718-957c-e8d63ed2d9ea',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'more information about al_color_cmyk please',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725548.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '38ef6502-cfb6-47fd-8aa2-f53bff5120ca',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'more information about al_load_font please',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725532.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '804706d8-987a-4ac9-a9fa-23df10fc6cde',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_font flags',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725523.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fd22c77e-7fc4-4b19-8a2d-16c7d4c29426',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I could not find a function to load ALLEGRO_COLOR, but there are several functions that take primitive parameters and return ALLEGRO_COLOR, such as\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_COLOR al_color_cmyk(float c, float m, float y, float k)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725460.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'da9d7f70-d973-4f7b-b1f6-12b04526ebfc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function should work:\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725353.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '82155698-adee-48bb-9d28-d731d10b44b7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'load ALLEGRO_COLOR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725321.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '394c05e2-4a52-4ba8-8496-c1c4a5728162',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'load ALLEGRO_FONT',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725317.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '594f8022-5c14-4e09-bd29-c68af16dd8c2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are several functions to display text, the simplest is al_draw_text\\n\\n```void al_draw_text(const ALLEGRO_FONT *font,\\n   ALLEGRO_COLOR color, float x, float y, int flags,\\n   char const *text) ```\\n\\nWrites the NUL-terminated string text onto the target bitmap at position  x, y, using the specified font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter can be 0 or one of the following flags:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_LEFT - Draw the text left-aligned (same as 0).\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_CENTRE - Draw the text centered around the given position.\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_RIGHT - Draw the text right-aligned to the given position.\\nIt can also be combined with this flag:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_INTEGER - Always draw text aligned to an integer pixel position. This was formerly the default behaviour. Since: 5.0.8, 5.1.4\\nThis function does not support newline characters (\\\\n), but you can use al_draw_multiline_text for multi line text output.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725257.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '30543fdc-10f5-44a1-9dd5-4be5eb848adc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how to display text with allegro',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725178.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f7a6ab2d-8ea0-42f9-b549-4420bef6b4f3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'If it helps, I was able to extract the following example that should Play an audio file.\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *sample=NULL;\\n\\n...\\n\\nif(!al_install_audio()){\\n      fprintf(stderr, \"failed to initialize audio!\\\\n\");\\n      return -1;\\n}\\n\\nif(!al_init_acodec_addon()){\\n      fprintf(stderr, \"failed to initialize audio codecs!\\\\n\");\\n      return -1;\\n}\\n\\t\\nif (!al_reserve_samples(1)){\\n      fprintf(stderr, \"failed to reserve samples!\\\\n\");\\n      return -1;\\n}\\n\\n...\\n\\t\\nsample = al_load_sample( \"footstep.wav\" );\\n\\n...\\n\\nal_play_sample(sample, 1.0, 0.0,1.0,ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP,NULL);```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539725068.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd777a8b8-f570-4642-9b0e-414f4d8e19b6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```bool al_init_acodec_addon(void)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724847.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '31bb1e45-9ecc-4efc-b99c-176c24d78296',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```bool al_install_audio(void)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724827.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '47995224-8a75-41e0-a5c0-55a0086edd81',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'function signature for al_init_acodec_addon()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724807.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2c31927b-0484-4732-9ccb-eed22e02b79e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'finction signature for al_install_audio()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724797.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '78e9c9c3-04ba-489a-968c-f670764ca492',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There a couple of other reasons this function might not work. Have you called al_install_audio() and al_init_acodec_addon()?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724777.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '66b5d886-dec0-4aa2-83e1-4212d9d58d22',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'If AUDIO_SAMPLE_PATH is a valid path, this call should return a sample.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724769.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '65001e89-bc34-4bf0-adc2-1dcac8217ee7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'spl = al_load_sample( AUDIO_SAMPLE_PATH );',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724674.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '792ff72b-db09-41a1-b2f0-7b6c8154edd5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'It looks like al_load_sample only returns NULL on failure. Could I see how you are calling the function?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724658.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a7d0ffe3-7da5-4a1a-abf7-f7cbbfc466bd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_sample is returning NULL',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724579.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ccf9d182-61f7-408b-a4c2-26d15f469327',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The function al_destroy_sample should work:\\n\\n```void al_destroy_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724379.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f014bdd7-bda2-4290-b820-cbb62b6bd568',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how to free ALLEGRO_SAMPLE',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724346.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '801b41fa-8ab4-4d71-b9af-85bb69b3c172',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how to free pointers allegro',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724336.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1e64a061-c346-4fd0-a2cf-858160cb6cea',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'An ALLEGRO_SAMPLE object stores the data necessary for playing pre-defined digital audio. It holds a user-specified PCM data buffer and information about its format (data length, depth, frequency, channel configuration). You can have the same ALLEGRO_SAMPLE playing multiple times simultaneously.\\n\\nSamples are often initialized with the function al_load_sample:\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *al_load_sample(const char *filename)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724257.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3653635a-6e0a-4639-95b8-7dec5134a0a2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is an ALLEGRO_SAMPLE',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724161.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fae49520-02b5-469e-8238-910619747450',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I was able to find an example function call:\\n\\n```al_play_sample(sample, 1.0, 0.0,1.0,ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP,NULL);```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724120.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1d856751-e62d-4b23-9ae0-d90e189fd707',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Regarding ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID variable ret_id - if non-NULL the variable which this points to will be assigned an id representing the sample being played. If al_play_sample returns  false, then the contents of ret_id are invalid and must not be used as argument to other functions.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724069.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0e5b4813-31c1-4e7b-a7de-179be65cdc36',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'That refers to an enum. Options are ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_ONCE, ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP, or ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_BIDIR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539724033.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0eca3f7a-0d6a-47b7-acf0-2e6e478f6421',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723981.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'adc00552-e65f-4d58-b8c8-85dee441f61f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723974.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '416ba734-12d1-4420-b2ab-2bfaf763aac5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The simplest method is al_play_sample\\n\\n```bool al_play_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl, float gain, float pan, float speed,\\n   ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE loop, ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID *ret_id)```\\n\\nPlays a sample on one of the sample instances created by al_reserve_samples. Returns true on success, false on failure. Playback may fail because all the reserved sample instances are currently used.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723924.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4d9a0fc1-57c7-4e54-941c-b1ac291d0fa2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How to play a sound with Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723875.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7a94131a-b66a-4c60-b9b6-b5e7428e0363',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"how to play a sound with allegro'\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723866.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b546e25d-a703-4f46-8e82-f6db964de3fd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The event types related to Key Events are ALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_DOWN and ALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_UP.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723411.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f9b68525-6b5f-48c2-84be-6b100466969b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are about 27 event types, related to KEY, MOUSE, JOYSTICK, TIME, DISPLAY, and TOUCH. The event types related to Key Events are ALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_DOWN and ALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_UP.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723373.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4f1bed89-0956-46e6-8532-d2f1592325be',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the allegro keyboard input event types',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723372.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0cb59e23-afd9-4d7d-8bb0-5b20e120c8ae',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what are all the possible allegro event types?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539723276.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b02b4027-7053-4745-8d58-17ff0301a7e0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_wait_for_event_timed:\\n\\nWait until the event queue specified is non-empty. If ret_event is not NULL, the first event in the queue will be copied into ret_event and removed from the queue. If ret_event is NULL the first event is left at the head of the queue.\\n\\nsecs determines approximately how many seconds to wait. If the call times out, false is returned. Otherwise, if an event ocurred, true is returned.\\n\\nFor compatibility with all platforms, secs must be 2,147,483.647 seconds or less.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722901.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6380dcb9-269f-4c08-9637-3c0969cdf800',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'please provide more information about al_wait_for_event_timed',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722872.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ee57badf-efdc-49f2-a9d7-a42b4c96f2ef',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Correction:\\n```ALLEGRO_EVENT_SOURCE *al_get_timer_event_source(ALLEGRO_TIMER *timer)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722807.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e47324e9-e35f-4b9b-ac75-0ba67d642df3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```void al_set_timer_speed(ALLEGRO_TIMER *timer, double new_speed_secs)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722741.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c9059361-aaa7-4b97-a340-74fb01510b34',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what is the function signature of al_get_timer_event_source',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722700.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b0c90a6b-1596-4c72-ae47-3a2290348603',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT\\n\\n```typedef struct ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT;```\\n\\nRepresent a timeout value. The size of the structure is known so it can be statically allocated. The contents are private.\\n\\nInitialized with\\n\\n```void al_init_timeout(ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT *timeout, double seconds)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722656.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f3e32d2f-56d3-43d4-b472-dc68e0463a6c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722619.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '030de005-89d1-4b17-871c-5667b8942514',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Do either of these functions look useful?\\n\\n```bool al_wait_for_event_timed(ALLEGRO_EVENT_QUEUE *queue,\\n   ALLEGRO_EVENT *ret_event, float secs)```\\n\\n```bool al_wait_for_event_until(ALLEGRO_EVENT_QUEUE *queue,\\n   ALLEGRO_EVENT *ret_event, ALLEGRO_TIMEOUT *timeout)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722555.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '95979583-33f4-4656-98af-17f13365aa33',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Is there a timeout to wait for an event?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722455.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7fa3ec7f-85b7-41f5-9f38-1b95567ad37f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The function\\n\\n```void al_wait_for_event(ALLEGRO_EVENT_QUEUE *queue, ALLEGRO_EVENT *ret_event)\\t```\\n\\nDescription: Wait until the event queue specified is non-empty. If ret_event is not NULL, the first event in the queue will be copied into ret_event and removed from the queue. If ret_event is NULL the first event is left at the head of the queue.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722265.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '15fa4ba1-4141-4ab5-9f69-9b6966cbbaff',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how to pop elements off the allegro event queue',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539722178.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0285981f-85c2-4d01-8973-2c48b39cc8ee',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ALLEGRO_KEY_LEFT and ALLEGRO_KEY_RIGHT are key codes, which are returned in the event.keyboard.keycode field of the ALLEGRO_KEY_DOWN and ALLEGRO_KEY_UP events.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721847.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e88f6f60-cb13-4103-a7aa-5bcc85c20c13',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the allegro event key right and allegro event key left variables called',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721761.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '898b5a2a-915f-41df-9199-9cc87235bc83',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Events and keyboard input are included in the allegro.h header.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721688.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3d56808a-25b8-4c41-a5ed-8a2f12a55643',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721629.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '427e4f3a-83aa-499b-bd33-3aabf0088e92',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What header do i need to include for the allegro key events',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721627.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8eb623e5-3454-4f69-b888-c55a6aab8d23',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You do not need to specifically register the keyboard, though it should be installed with\\n```bool al_install_keyboard(void)```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721158.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '87ada5ff-804a-420e-8936-3523e1f33586',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Something like ALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_DOWN? If you have an event ```ev```, you can check the value of ```ev.keyboard.keycode```.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721088.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '53b1531b-af66-4dca-a5e6-e230110681dc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I register keyboard events with allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721065.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '12e71b1f-6138-4006-9583-8fb97727ac1f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '<@UB659D0FM> do you hear me',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539721002.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3b043187-6649-4a44-a5a6-2d099fb217ac',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Apiza are you there',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539720982.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b16b0224-d8bb-4e0c-822d-5888643945aa',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I register keyboard events?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539720944.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '29065618-4249-48db-be58-f1724aca52a7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I get keyboard events',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539720905.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e392a66c-47db-48de-871d-ffd302e64b42',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hi! I’m Apiza, a virtual assistant designed to help you use a new API. How can I help you?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539720680.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '9a6f1118-4702-466e-b709-f35494371ece',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hello Apiza',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDFECTDHS',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539720672.000100'}],\n",
       "   'has_more': False}},\n",
       " 17: {'library': 'allegro',\n",
       "  'metadata': {'wizard': '01', 'programmer': '17'},\n",
       "  'score': {0: 2, 1: 2, 2: 1, 3: 2, 4: 0, 5: 0, 6: 0},\n",
       "  'entry': {0: 'German',\n",
       "   1: '',\n",
       "   2: '20',\n",
       "   3: '17',\n",
       "   4: 'Yes',\n",
       "   5: 'No',\n",
       "   6: '',\n",
       "   7: 'Novice'},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 5, 1: 4, 2: 3, 3: 3, 4: 5, 5: 5, 6: 4, 7: 4, 8: 2},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': 'e5aa039d-a6fb-4649-bc02-5e23ed441812',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I do not think so. I found the following example in which al_load_bitmap without al_create_bitmap:\\n\\n```\\nALLEGRO_BITMAP  *image   = NULL;\\n\\n...\\n\\nal_init_image_addon()\\n\\n...\\n\\nimage = al_load_bitmap(\"image.png\");```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539894172.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '25ddc03a-76eb-4aed-9617-0cd03e310b7e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Do I need to initialize bitmap before calling al_load_bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893930.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5ef27f38-b815-4a43-a895-1c71ec74c50e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_get_bitmap_width\\n\\n```int al_get_bitmap_width(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap)```\\n\\nReturns the width of a bitmap in pixels.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893632.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '179cb950-e4bc-4527-aab0-9eb34748bc00',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'All al_draw_* functions draw onto the target bitmap. The target bitmap defaults to the display, unless otherwise specified. The target bitmap can be set with al_set_target_bitmap.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893608.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '367adcd1-0499-40de-b22a-7e3179ae1d3a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I get the width of a bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893582.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '59a56a01-a17d-45cb-9f64-17d04c325d24',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I draw a bitmap onto another bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893539.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e6099992-3a29-4e5f-81fd-49c116f72462',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'To summarize:\\n\\nThis function selects the bitmap to which all subsequent drawing operations in the calling thread will draw to.\\n\\nWould you like the full description?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893512.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'abb83f5b-70e9-45bc-ab51-b030a2f4aafa',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What does al_set_target_bitmap do?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893454.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3943f06b-6114-4d68-81d7-eab6928211bb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The parameters for al_draw_scaled_bitmap:\\n\\nsx - source x\\nsy - source y\\nsw - source width\\nsh - source height\\ndx - destination x\\ndy - destination y\\ndw - destination width\\ndh - destination height\\nflags - same as for al_draw_bitmap',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893392.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a03451a7-6af8-49f0-88b0-c7fdedc7065b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the parameters sx, sy, sw, sh, etc.?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893368.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '11ace5e6-1fc1-41ed-a17a-ca6c3b288937',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are a few methods that fit:\\n\\nal_draw_scaled_rotated_bitmap\\nal_draw_tinted_scaled_rotated_bitmap\\nal_draw_tinted_scaled_rotated_bitmap_region\\nal_draw_scaled_bitmap\\nal_draw_tinted_scaled_bitmap\\n\\nThe simplest method is al_draw_scaled_bitmap:\\n\\n```void al_draw_scaled_bitmap(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap,\\n   float sx, float sy, float sw, float sh,\\n   float dx, float dy, float dw, float dh, int flags)```\\n\\nDraws a scaled version of the given bitmap to the target bitmap.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893346.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e0c6fdbe-ed19-421f-b637-4c872ed89b4c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I scale and draw a bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893300.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '33482758-669e-46fa-9b64-c1820ba197d3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The simplest function is al_load_bitmap:\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_BITMAP *al_load_bitmap(const char *filename)```\\n\\nLoads an image file into a new ALLEGRO_BITMAP.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893124.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c8d16870-eabd-45d6-87ba-921a85df5ddb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I load a bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893089.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b2a2702a-c5e5-422c-9ee4-af1a6c9ec8e9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_install_mouse\\n\\n```bool al_install_mouse(void)```\\n\\nInstall a mouse driver.\\n\\nReturns true if successful. If a driver was already installed, nothing happens and true is returned.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539893005.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '37fabf5d-f58f-4f4c-b1ba-d2636e40da11',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I install the mouse driver?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892984.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5dc9eb4b-88fa-42b4-9198-dc6c6e8c60e3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```bool al_get_timer_started(const ALLEGRO_TIMER *timer)```\\n\\nReturn true if the timer specified is currently started.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892936.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7337afc1-b35a-46b0-bf4c-ab0880939b12',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '``` void al_resume_timer(ALLEGRO_TIMER *timer)```\\n\\nResume the timer specified.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892917.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '188cf7a8-911f-42d2-94ed-70d118ee0929',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the return type of al_get_timer_started?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892916.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5e13d973-3bbc-4ac2-a3d5-f23d76a50f09',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found a few methods to get information about an ALLEGRO_TIMER :\\n\\nal_get_timer_started\\nal_get_timer_count\\nal_get_timer_speed\\nal_get_timer_event_source\\n\\nI could not find any that return an ALLEGRO_STATE .',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892894.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e7ecaf2f-b41d-4de9-abe4-4722d8fe1a98',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I resume a timer after stopping it?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892840.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '14cd7a5e-edf5-4030-a52c-18d33bbaf0dc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I get the state of a timer?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892807.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b8287155-1afc-4cae-a2c0-8455f6f90eb3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are several Mouse event types:\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_AXES\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_BUTTON_DOWN\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_BUTTON_UP\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_WARPED\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_ENTER_DISPLAY\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_LEAVE_DISPLAY',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892723.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '021c80b7-e5d8-4485-abe9-a26f769693c1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I was able to put together an example to Render text:\\n\\n```al_init_font_addon(); // initialize the font addon\\nal_init_ttf_addon();// initialize the ttf (True Type Font) addon\\n...\\nALLEGRO_DISPLAY *display = al_create_display(640,480);\\n...\\nALLEGRO_FONT *font = al_load_ttf_font(\"pirulen.ttf\",72,0 );\\n...\\nal_draw_text(font, al_map_rgb(255,255,255), 640/2, (480/4),ALLEGRO_ALIGN_CENTRE, \"Your Text Here!\");```\\n\\nDoes this look useful?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892646.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd750c926-ff1e-4bfa-94a0-4e7b7f821456',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_stop_timer should work:\\n\\n```void al_stop_timer(ALLEGRO_TIMER *timer)```\\n\\nStop the timer specified.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892616.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a749e815-d840-48ad-ada9-1796b3f2e91a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I register mouse events?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892585.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e4fca072-0270-4a3a-acc2-a02b689220e9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I stop a timer?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892519.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '11f8165a-2131-4908-94aa-3fb2d0f2c475',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure, I will try to put together an example.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892502.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b1a6f6bb-2c30-4866-ba69-a40eea035181',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you give me an example to render text?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892464.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '22e19f24-1779-42a4-9278-6d16c3177d04',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'void al_draw_text\\n\\nVoid return',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892258.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f9ff4faf-184b-4be0-981c-98c690e6f4dc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the return type of al_draw_text?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892209.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b3192476-4110-457c-89ea-312456751d9d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_get_display_width returns an int. This value can cast to a float',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892151.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ec6e5b3d-c835-4b79-844e-cb1262fa8839',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I convert an integer from al_get_display_width to a float for coordinate x?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892039.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f473fd45-233f-4a98-8490-85854f4e4cf2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'These methods should work:\\n\\n```int al_get_display_width(ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *display)```\\n\\nGets the width of the display.\\n\\n```int al_get_display_height(ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *display)```\\n\\nGets the height of the display.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539892003.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4f14a927-8ffa-4c0c-b561-9907eff4f236',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I get the height and width of the window?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891964.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3a2dfb93-15c1-444e-a622-06692d77e663',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'x and y refer to the pixel coordinates within the display. The coordinate (0,0) refers to the upper-left-most pixel of the display.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891942.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5bd915e4-77e6-4819-bb15-13a362e7eb0d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```ALLEGRO_COLOR al_map_rgb(\\n   unsigned char r, unsigned char g, unsigned char b)```\\n\\nConvert r, g, b (ranging from 0-255) into an ALLEGRO_COLOR, using 255 for alpha.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891875.000300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7d72456c-fcae-4985-b0e0-94e66e9d957b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the minimum and maximum value for x and y?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891875.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e8cbdfd0-8976-4684-90e7-602b940a3eb1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I am not sure about the coordinate system for x and y .',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891857.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '64f0002a-f0b3-42cd-879b-91bc1e3d4ba9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the parameters for al_map_rgb?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891809.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2cab7386-7ea2-43fd-bca1-d1d0d3d381eb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```typedef struct ALLEGRO_COLOR ALLEGRO_COLOR;```\\n\\nAn ALLEGRO_COLOR structure describes a color in a device independent way. Use al_map_rgb et al. and al_unmap_rgb et al. to translate from and to various color representations.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891764.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f458cb71-ac42-4c0c-bc11-e5fe56c3978b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the coordinate system for x and y?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891743.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '277cc130-dd12-4564-b839-928802cbc0f6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The x and y variables are floats. The function al_draw_text Writes the NUL-terminated string text onto the target bitmap at position x, y, using the specified font.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891722.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '470126d8-22fc-4f2c-9300-6b98a77833a6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are possible values for ALLEGRO_COLOR?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891680.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e2019b72-61bf-482a-b12d-bf08ea2ccf08',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the values x and y in al_draw_text?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891615.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4372b15e-6b81-4eea-bf21-e538963bff56',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_destroy_font\\n\\n```void al_destroy_font(ALLEGRO_FONT *f)```\\n\\nFrees the memory being used by a font structure. Does nothing if passed NULL.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891576.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '269f7ad4-9d94-4e4c-9164-1eb197c75be2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I free a font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891538.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd41e8cae-3eec-4c0b-91a6-d7bf233495a5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found this list of supported values for the int flags:\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_KERNING - Do not use any kerning even if the font file supports it.\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_MONOCHROME - Load as a monochrome font (which means no anti-aliasing of the font is done).\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_AUTOHINT - Disable the Auto Hinter which is enabled by default in newer versions of FreeType. Since: 5.0.6, 5.1.2',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891489.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a4ca9d5d-c822-4865-b6be-968870f5a3da',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found a description of the int size for the similar method al_load_ttf_font:\\n\\nThe size parameter determines the size the font will be rendered at, specified in pixels.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891428.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '53f8415c-4759-4db2-bdf5-408d2d7525dd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are possible values for flags?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891412.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4b0064ff-3b57-40f5-8e0f-e1b9aee113ac',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the size of a font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891377.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7f2a1b4c-e7df-44de-af89-a24945e6e17f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The size parameter is an int.\\n\\nThe flags parameter is passed through to either of those functions. Bitmap and TTF fonts are also affected by the current bitmap flags at the time the font is loaded.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891336.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ef84c510-72b6-42d2-804c-6b815c9e7672',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the parameters size and flags?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891290.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8d3008bb-0802-4be8-9a78-2b927f31aaf0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The simplest method to Load a font is al_load_font:\\n\\n```ALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)```\\n\\nLoads a font from disk.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891229.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd4d215ff-0bb7-4281-b5c6-659d6c0ea3c6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I load a font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891204.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '306e1c3d-bc95-485b-8ba6-022a809479e8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '```bool al_init_font_addon(void)```\\n\\nInitialise the font addon.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891133.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3fd6c0d9-f788-473a-9667-6dfee42bcbe3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I initialize the ALLEGRO_FONT add-on?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891115.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'cc35df24-970c-4b93-9dcb-89d02ac36423',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The simplest method to Display text in window frame is al_draw_text:\\n\\n```void al_draw_text(const ALLEGRO_FONT *font,\\n   ALLEGRO_COLOR color, float x, float y, int flags,\\n   char const *text) ```\\n\\nThis requires the ALLEGRO_FONT add-on.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891092.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2878a708-4b96-4306-9262-b451b9cabc2b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How can I display text within the window frame?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539891013.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b1ebdd7f-7f36-4e74-9e3a-90e688c0c64e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ret_id - if non-NULL the variable which this points to will be assigned an id representing the sample being played. If al_play_sample returns false, then the contents of ret_id are invalid and must not be used as argument to other functions.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890909.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1258dc00-f8fb-4edf-95a9-3ee2fc2f87c8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the purpose of the last parameter in al_play_sample? (ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID *ret_id)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890895.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '760d1b73-2b15-4320-a541-6d06c5b48bbb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'enum ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE\\n\\nDescription: Sample and stream playback mode.\\n\\nValues:\\nALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_ONCE\\nALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP\\nALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_BIDIR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890884.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f990e140-af7e-4ade-b523-fa0c60d01338',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are possible values for ALLEGRO_PLAYNODE?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890847.000100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '16706e4a-6d32-4f94-b67f-136651319a8e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_destroy_sample should work:\\n\\n```void al_destroy_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl)```\\n\\nFree the sample data structure.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890814.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'dfbb3b2e-3c87-404f-9e85-79958aaf098f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'is there a function to free samples?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UDH7Q6XNY',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890780.000200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '711fc974-70cc-466f-b13c-615395bd3681',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_reserve_samples Returns true on success, false on error.\\n\\nal_load_sample Returns the sample on success, NULL on failure.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1539890738.000100'},\n",
