       "     'text': 'ALLEGRO_EVENT_MOUSE_BUTTON_DOWN\\n\\nA mouse button was pressed.\\n\\nmouse.x (int)\\nx-coordinate\\nmouse.y (int)\\ny-coordinate\\nmouse.z (int)\\nz-coordinate\\nmouse.w (int)\\nw-coordinate\\nmouse.button (unsigned)\\nThe mouse button which was pressed, numbering from 1.\\nmouse.pressure (float)\\nPressure, ranging from 0.0 to 1.0.\\nmouse.display (ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *)\\nThe display which had mouse focus.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171651.014900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '442ec17e-6df9-4396-86c5-1356eec773b9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the event type of a mouse click?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171592.014700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '331f3582-3913-4888-ad6f-97973354d1bb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"ALLEGRO_MOUSE_STATE's buttons field will tell you whether or not it has been clicked:\\n\\ntypedef struct ALLEGRO_MOUSE_STATE ALLEGRO_MOUSE_STATE;\\n\\nPublic fields (read only):\\n\\nx - mouse x position\\ny - mouse y position\\nw, z - mouse wheel position (2D 'ball')\\nbuttons - mouse buttons bitfield\\n\\nThe zeroth bit is set if the primary mouse button is held down, the first bit is set if the secondary mouse button is held down, and so on.\\n\\npressure - pressure, ranging from 0.0 to 1.0\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171540.014400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2adf858d-492d-4cd0-851a-1aa04d28c1f1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What does a mouse click event look like?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171463.014200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '28ca5f62-cba6-4cca-9f3b-6d76c45a4644',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_install_mouse should do that:\\n\\nbool al_install_mouse(void)\\n\\nInstall a mouse driver.\\n\\nReturns true if successful. If a driver was already installed, nothing happens and true is returned.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171441.014000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8a45ddc6-ce28-4801-ab43-126d3399eef3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I install the mouse subsystem?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171392.013800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '690ff5e4-ab7c-431c-935e-84d76deb245d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_get_mouse_event_source will give you the mouse event source:\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_SOURCE *al_get_mouse_event_source(void)\\n\\nRetrieve the mouse event source. All mouse events are generated by this event source.\\n\\nReturns NULL if the mouse subsystem was not installed.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171369.013600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b82bf61e-2e77-44bd-81ab-532ba9fea676',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I capture mouse events?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547171283.013400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'aa200ef4-7b71-40fc-a57e-2f41fd93886a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"al_draw_rotated_bitmap should let you rotate a bitmap:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_rotated_bitmap(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap,\\n   float cx, float cy, float dx, float dy, float angle, int flags)\\n\\nDraws a rotated version of the given bitmap to the target bitmap. The bitmap is rotated by 'angle' radians clockwise.\\n\\nThe point at cx/cy relative to the upper left corner of the bitmap will be drawn at dx/dy and the bitmap is rotated around this point. If cx,cy is 0,0 the bitmap will rotate around its upper left corner.\\n\\ncx - center x (relative to the bitmap)\\ncy - center y (relative to the bitmap)\\ndx - destination x\\ndy - destination y\\nangle - angle by which to rotate (radians)\\nflags - same as for al_draw_bitmap\\nExample\\n\\nfloat w = al_get_bitmap_width(bitmap);\\nfloat h = al_get_bitmap_height(bitmap);\\nal_draw_rotated_bitmap(bitmap, w / 2, h / 2, x, y, ALLEGRO_PI / 2, 0);\\nThe above code draws the bitmap centered on x/y and rotates it 90° clockwise.\\n\\nSee al_draw_bitmap for a note on restrictions on which bitmaps can be drawn where.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170660.013100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e1409b7c-6604-453c-90d5-5d1356b58b16',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I rotate a bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170615.012900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3735b0d9-8449-4156-970f-d2d2818e820c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_get_bitmap_height and al_get_bitmap_width should allow you to do that:\\n\\nint al_get_bitmap_height(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap)\\n\\nReturns the height of a bitmap in pixels.\\n\\nint al_get_bitmap_width(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap)\\n\\nReturns the width of a bitmap in pixels.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170475.012700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '627ea097-71f9-4633-a933-9fa420ea2803',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"How do I get a bitmap's width and height?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170383.012500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a1c7e554-57e2-4ec4-80fc-8d8fe3b9b80d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_draw_scaled_bitmap should allow you to scale a bitmap:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_scaled_bitmap(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap,\\n   float sx, float sy, float sw, float sh,\\n   float dx, float dy, float dw, float dh, int flags)\\n\\nDraws a scaled version of the given bitmap to the target bitmap.\\n\\nsx - source x\\nsy - source y\\nsw - source width\\nsh - source height\\ndx - destination x\\ndy - destination y\\ndw - destination width\\ndh - destination height\\nflags - same as for al_draw_bitmap\\nSee al_draw_bitmap for a note on restrictions on which bitmaps can be drawn where.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170320.012200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd0d73286-35e8-4837-8ebc-a1946cff9927',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I scale a bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170278.012000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '15c850ae-195f-45b8-9201-30361cc88d4e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_draw_bitmap should allow you to draw a second bitmap over the first:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_bitmap(ALLEGRO_BITMAP *bitmap, float dx, float dy, int flags)\\n\\nDraws an unscaled, unrotated bitmap at the given position to the current target bitmap (see al_set_target_bitmap).\\n\\nflags can be a combination of:\\n\\nALLEGRO_FLIP_HORIZONTAL - flip the bitmap about the y-axis\\nALLEGRO_FLIP_VERTICAL - flip the bitmap about the x-axis\\n\\nNote: The current target bitmap must be a different bitmap. Drawing a bitmap to itself (or to a sub-bitmap of itself) or drawing a sub-bitmap to its parent (or another sub-bitmap of its parent) are not currently supported. To copy part of a bitmap into the same bitmap simply use a temporary bitmap instead.\\n\\nNote: The backbuffer (or a sub-bitmap thereof) can not be transformed, blended or tinted. If you need to draw the backbuffer draw it to a temporary bitmap first with no active transformation (except translation). Blending and tinting settings/parameters will be ignored. This does not apply when drawing into a memory bitmap.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170245.011800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e73dbf90-5819-4cf2-8cec-a2bce66a23f8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I want to draw one bitmap over another',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170128.011600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '77528436-5dfc-4636-963c-cb98186546c6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What do you want to do with the two bitmaps?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170116.011300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0535ab2e-ffff-4cc2-bdfd-690a664d2f5e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I've loaded the bitmap, how do I blit it onto another bitmap?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547170044.011100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7593e49c-ac61-4113-95f3-0f14a387f6d2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"As long as you've called al_init_image_addon you should already have PNG support. Are you having trouble loading a PNG file?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169982.010800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '775d522b-507e-469e-9f60-8a932f9113d6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I need PNG support, how do I load that?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169901.010600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3e31b730-bc65-4ad5-b7ae-ea719a064818',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to call al_init_image_addon:\\n\\nbool al_init_image_addon(void)\\n\\nInitializes the image addon. This registers bitmap format handlers for al_load_bitmap, al_load_bitmap_f, al_save_bitmap, al_save_bitmap_f.\\n\\nThe following types are built into the Allegro image addon and guaranteed to be available: BMP, DDS, PCX, TGA. Every platform also supports JPEG and PNG via external dependencies.\\n\\nOther formats may be available depending on the operating system and installed libraries, but are not guaranteed and should not be assumed to be universally available.\\n\\nThe DDS format is only supported to load from, and only if the DDS file contains textures compressed in the DXT1, DXT3 and DXT5 formats. Note that when loading a DDS file, the created bitmap will always be a video bitmap and will have the pixel format matching the format in the file.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169833.010400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '24ef1535-822f-43d2-bbd1-9c94aa2ebb09',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Do I need to call anything before calling al_load_bitmap?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169789.010200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b4b8e75c-8ac0-41de-94e2-d23e73da9a61',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You should be able to load an image from a file with al_load_bitmap:\\n\\nALLEGRO_BITMAP *al_load_bitmap(const char *filename)\\n\\nLoads an image file into a new ALLEGRO_BITMAP. The file type is determined by the extension, except if the file has no extension in which case al_identify_bitmap is used instead.\\n\\nReturns NULL on error.\\n\\nThis is the same as calling al_load_bitmap_flags with a flags parameter of 0.\\n\\nNote: the core Allegro library does not support any image file formats by default. You must use the allegro_image addon, or register your own format handler.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169746.009900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e707559b-d660-41f5-b43a-db5838f94256',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I load an image?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169674.009700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'df5d8cde-cb5a-4bca-8a25-f352b5d13cde',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You may need to call al_init_font_addon and/or al_init_ttf_addon, along with al_create_display in order to display the font once it has loaded.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169477.009500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3110ad61-5bcb-415d-8aa0-fba6d3817a19',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Do I need to call anything before calling al_load_font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169377.009300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'da3d750f-d209-4837-a98e-ce2cfe6c7059',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The size parameter determines the size the font will be rendered at, specified in pixels. The standard font size is measured in units per EM, if you instead want to specify the size as the total height of glyphs in pixels, pass it as a negative value.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169244.008900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd925586c-90da-44a9-8642-f5b4d14da802',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is the size parameter in al_load_font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169182.008700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'af174569-23e3-4b73-9d1b-1c60e377783a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Are you sure the filename and size are correct?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169145.008400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '89254a44-d821-489e-939d-98eb3358d6a7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_font is returning NULL. What are some possible reasons?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547169092.008200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '83b20daf-8cf6-45f1-abe8-9ec3f47553a5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_draw_text should allow you to display text:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_text(const ALLEGRO_FONT *font,\\n   ALLEGRO_COLOR color, float x, float y, int flags,\\n   char const *text)\\n\\nWrites the NUL-terminated string text onto the target bitmap at position x, y, using the specified font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter can be 0 or one of the following flags:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_LEFT - Draw the text left-aligned (same as 0).\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_CENTRE - Draw the text centered around the given position.\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_RIGHT - Draw the text right-aligned to the given position.\\nIt can also be combined with this flag:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_INTEGER - Always draw text aligned to an integer pixel position. This was formerly the default behaviour. Since: 5.0.8, 5.1.4\\nThis function does not support newline characters (\\\\n), but you can use al_draw_multiline_text for multi line text output.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168863.007900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7be0fc80-138f-4002-93ea-7ac9790b75b1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I display text?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168807.007700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f6983143-43b5-4c91-9a13-717c90f93b29',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'It will take the following if you pass the name of a known bitmap format:\\n\\nALLEGRO_NO_PREMULTIPLIED_ALPHA\\nBy default, Allegro pre-multiplies the alpha channel of an image with the images color data when it loads it. Typically that would look something like this:\\n\\nr = get_float_byte();\\ng = get_float_byte();\\nb = get_float_byte();\\na = get_float_byte();\\n\\nr = r * a;\\ng = g * a;\\nb = b * a;\\n\\nset_image_pixel(x, y, r, g, b, a);\\nThe reason for this can be seen in the Allegro example ex_premulalpha, ie, using pre-multiplied alpha gives more accurate color results in some cases. To use alpha blending with images loaded with pre-multiplied alpha, you would use the default blending mode, which is set with al_set_blender(ALLEGRO_ADD, ALLEGRO_ONE, ALLEGRO_INVERSE_ALPHA).\\n\\nThe ALLEGRO_NO_PREMULTIPLIED_ALPHA flag being set will ensure that images are not loaded with alpha pre-multiplied, but are loaded with color values direct from the image. That looks like this:\\n\\nr = get_float_byte();\\ng = get_float_byte();\\nb = get_float_byte();\\na = get_float_byte();\\n\\nset_image_pixel(x, y, r, g, b, a);\\nTo draw such an image using regular alpha blending, you would use al_set_blender(ALLEGRO_ADD, ALLEGRO_ALPHA, ALLEGRO_INVERSE_ALPHA) to set the correct blender. This has some caveats. First, as mentioned above, drawing such an image can result in less accurate color blending (when drawing an image with linear filtering on, the edges will be darker than they should be). Second, the behaviour is somewhat confusing, which is explained in the example below.\\n\\n// Load and create bitmaps with an alpha channel\\nal_set_new_bitmap_format(ALLEGRO_PIXEL_FORMAT_ANY_32_WITH_ALPHA);\\n// Load some bitmap with alpha in it\\nbmp = al_load_bitmap(\"some_alpha_bitmap.png\");\\n// We will draw to this buffer and then draw this buffer to the screen\\ntmp_buffer = al_create_bitmap(SCREEN_W, SCREEN_H);\\n// Set the buffer as the target and clear it\\nal_set_target_bitmap(tmp_buffer);\\nal_clear_to_color(al_map_rgba_f(0, 0, 0, 1));\\n// Draw the bitmap to the temporary buffer\\nal_draw_bitmap(bmp, 0, 0, 0);\\n// Finally, draw the buffer to the screen\\n// The output will look incorrect (may take close inspection\\n// depending on the bitmap -- it may also be very obvious)\\nal_set_target_bitmap(al_get_backbuffer(display));\\nal_draw_bitmap(tmp_buffer, 0, 0, 0);\\nTo explain further, if you have a pixel with 0.5 alpha, and you\\'re using (ALLEGRO_ADD, ALLEGRO_ALPHA, ALLEGRO_INVERSE_ALPHA) for blending, the formula is:\\n\\na = da * dst + sa * src\\nExpands to:\\n\\nresult_a = dst_a * (1-0.5) + 0.5 * 0.5\\nSo if you draw the image to the temporary buffer, it is blended once resulting in 0.75 alpha, then drawn again to the screen, blended in the same way, resulting in a pixel has 0.1875 as an alpha value.\\n\\nOtherwise it will use the following:\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_KERNING - Do not use any kerning even if the font file supports it.\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_MONOCHROME - Load as a monochrome font (which means no anti-aliasing of the font is done).\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_AUTOHINT - Disable the Auto Hinter which is enabled by default in newer versions of FreeType. Since: 5.0.6, 5.1.2',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168774.007400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b423bae1-b91d-4c04-95d6-d9c2782b68b3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What flags can be passed to al_load_font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168604.007200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '42168d3c-c43a-414f-b94b-a143b4ecbe69',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_font will allow you to load a font:\\n\\nALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)\\n\\nLoads a font from disk. This will use al_load_bitmap_font_flags if you pass the name of a known bitmap format, or else al_load_ttf_font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter is passed through to either of those functions. Bitmap and TTF fonts are also affected by the current bitmap flags at the time the font is loaded.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168557.006800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ec950684-6355-4b9e-92b6-88efb9be6789',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I load a font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168481.006600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '476ef78d-a3d6-4f81-a5db-6d6404531e99',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll also want to call al_reserve_samples:\\n\\nbool al_reserve_samples(int reserve_samples)\\n\\nReserves a number of sample instances, attaching them to the default mixer. If no default mixer is set when this function is called, then it will create one and attach it to the default voice. If no default voice has been set, it, too, will be created.\\n\\nIf you call this function a second time with a smaller number of samples, then the excess internal sample instances will be destroyed causing some sounds to stop and some instances returned by al_lock_sample_id to be invalidated.\\n\\nThis diagram illustrates the structures that are set up:\\n\\n                                      sample instance 1\\n                                    / sample instance 2\\ndefault voice &lt;-- default mixer &lt;---         .\\n                                    \\\\        .\\n                                      sample instance N\\n\\nReturns true on success, false on error. al_install_audio must have been called first.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168392.006400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6ae7714e-5da3-417c-99a2-05531853193e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Now al_load_sample is segfaulting. Is there anything else I need to do before calling al_load_sample?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168304.006200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '35926eec-7386-4eba-914a-80cb16a2581e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_sample returns NULL on failure. Have you called al_init_acodec_addon?\\n\\nbool al_init_acodec_addon(void)\\n\\nThis function registers all the known audio file type handlers for al_load_sample, al_save_sample, al_load_audio_stream, etc.\\n\\nDepending on what libraries are available, the full set of recognised extensions is: .wav, .flac, .ogg, .opus, .it, .mod, .s3m, .xm, .voc.\\n\\nLimitations:\\n\\nSaving is only supported for wav files.\\n\\nThe wav file loader currently only supports 8/16 bit little endian PCM files. 16 bits are used when saving wav files. Use flac files if more precision is required.\\n\\nModule files (.it, .mod, .s3m, .xm) are often composed with streaming in mind, and sometimes cannot be easily rendered into a finite length sample. Therefore they cannot be loaded with al_load_sample/al_load_sample_f and must be streamed with al_load_audio_stream or al_load_audio_stream_f.\\n\\n.voc file streaming is unimplemented.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168141.005700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd9471dfa-1e36-4e57-8016-b6ef10ab4cbd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_load_sample is returning NULL. Is there any way to find out why?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168027.005500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0a680d21-30c0-480d-aa55-5eea5bd92b44',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I don't think you can get more detailed information than you're already getting. Is there any error in particular you're having trouble with?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547168000.005100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f2f8e577-e93b-418c-b3f5-3236a02ff4ef',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I get more detailed error information from Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167871.004900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a67a30c9-8eba-4c2f-886f-bce5e036c468',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You should be able to load a sample with al_load_sample:\\n\\nALLEGRO_SAMPLE *al_load_sample(const char *filename)\\n\\nLoads a few different audio file formats based on their extension.\\n\\nNote that this stores the entire file in memory at once, which may be time consuming. To read the file as it is needed, use al_load_audio_stream.\\n\\nReturns the sample on success, NULL on failure.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167523.004600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a1443900-3bbc-48c9-8a1d-b69bbd8904da',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I load a sample in Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167451.004400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a3e975e1-cbb6-43f9-8845-8cd3e08821af',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You should be able to play a sound with al_play_sample:\\n\\nbool al_play_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl, float gain, float pan, float speed,\\n   ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE loop, ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID *ret_id)\\n\\nPlays a sample on one of the sample instances created by al_reserve_samples. Returns true on success, false on failure. Playback may fail because all the reserved sample instances are currently used.\\n\\nParameters:\\n\\ngain - relative volume at which the sample is played; 1.0 is normal.\\npan - 0.0 is centred, -1.0 is left, 1.0 is right, or ALLEGRO_AUDIO_PAN_NONE.\\nspeed - relative speed at which the sample is played; 1.0 is normal.\\nloop - ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_ONCE, ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP, or ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_BIDIR\\nret_id - if non-NULL the variable which this points to will be assigned an id representing the sample being played. If al_play_sample returns false, then the contents of ret_id are invalid and must not be used as argument to other functions.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167426.004100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '439286b5-159c-4cb6-9004-3edc247c00e0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I play a sound in Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167367.003900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a825a93d-7477-4a75-a387-d0d689874a2f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_install_keyboard() should work.\\n\\nbool al_install_keyboard(void)\\n\\nInstall a keyboard driver. Returns true if successful. If a driver was already installed, nothing happens and true is returned.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167317.003700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '37256e53-9470-4521-b3bf-7332b0898e3f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I call al_install_keyboard?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167238.003500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bde95e1f-99db-4d81-b0e7-608146e9495c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Have you called al_install_keyboard?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167223.003300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ddeaf478-bec1-4070-b8a3-b9dd23f7c9b2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_get_keyboard is failing with \"Assertion `new_keyboard_driver\\' failed\". What might be the cause of this?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547167177.003100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5d55020f-fabd-4702-bd2f-7154a6095feb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The keycodes for the arrow keys are the following:\\n\\nALLEGRO_KEY_LEFT\\nALLEGRO_KEY_RIGHT\\nALLEGRO_KEY_UP\\nALLEGRO_KEY_DOWN',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166981.002500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '378f82b2-53cf-40d9-9b10-1d95234336da',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What are the keycodes for up, down, left and right?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166939.002300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '86b3fae8-f2a9-4577-9516-0030615e11a1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ev.keyboard.keycode will get you the keycode for event ev.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166920.002000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'adfd5151-cbfb-4da7-ba15-fb233038bdd4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I access the keycode from an event object?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166866.001800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bb78f47a-ef36-4f56-9b9f-13c52eef7e18',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'One of the following:\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_DOWN\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_UP\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_CHAR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166810.001300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1ad6d119-bbd8-4f2b-8b27-ef4b28548f3c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What event type is a keyboard event?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166743.001100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '25029390-2019-4476-893f-6d7bf6632922',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Yes, you'll want to use something like:\\n\\nal_register_event_source(event_queue, al_get_keyboard_event_source());\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166691.000900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0b1788bb-59d8-466f-b1ba-7e00895c403b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can I use keyboard events as an event source?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166486.000700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'be271cab-1322-4a79-84ff-f4e9788cca8f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll most likely want to be using al_key_down:\\n\\nbool al_key_down(const ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE *state, int keycode)\\n\\nReturn true if the key specified was held down in the state specified.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166453.000400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd423bbb4-0008-4646-838d-4ea4ab123e77',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do I register key events?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFC9DV487',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547166391.000200'}],\n",
       "   'has_more': False}},\n",
       " 28: {'library': 'allegro',\n",
       "  'metadata': {'wizard': '06', 'programmer': '28'},\n",
       "  'score': {0: 2, 1: 2, 2: 2, 3: 0, 4: 0, 5: 0, 6: 0},\n",
       "  'entry': {},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 5, 1: 5, 2: 5, 3: 5, 4: 4, 5: 5, 6: 4, 7: 5, 8: 4},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': 'fa5cc76f-2b74-4481-b70d-a271b32fcc9b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you load a .png into a bitmap',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547319228.013400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '98802b58-9c10-4f6c-a236-c4a59081d989',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Great!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547319111.013100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ab2a8ad9-9645-45a4-a064-24bf40050d0b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ok, it works',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547319100.012900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '87258bd9-cd27-4db3-a167-d5d5bb8fdb2a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'nevermind',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547318866.012700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '810de1db-b3c0-4a73-8a70-297fe1ec490b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What to do if al_draw_text produces no result?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547318783.012500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1d8d819b-248c-451f-b394-f79d0322442b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ok, nevermind',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547318468.012100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6e2f4324-f589-4ccc-babd-6e57083fdaa0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"It seems like that's most likely a problem with your virtual machine. What size display are you using?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547318442.011800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8e8b1b26-e313-4a15-bb9d-6782c18b4440',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'why would al_draw_text() produce the warning \"VERR_BUFFER_OVERFLOW',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547318305.011600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8ec38d75-498f-47c0-af9c-d8a4912b546d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'al_map_rgb should allow you to create an ALLEGRO_COLOR:\\n\\nALLEGRO_COLOR al_map_rgb(\\n   unsigned char r, unsigned char g, unsigned char b)\\n\\nConvert r, g, b (ranging from 0-255) into an ALLEGRO_COLOR, using 255 for alpha.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317832.010900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd6ef49ed-cf70-43e8-88f1-a1ef38e6151e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you use ALLEGRO_COLOR?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317714.010700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ea516c67-5f30-4b18-bd60-e9380bd6b400',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"To draw text you'll probably want to use al_draw_text:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_text(const ALLEGRO_FONT *font,\\n   ALLEGRO_COLOR color, float x, float y, int flags,\\n   char const *text)\\n\\nWrites the NUL-terminated string text onto the target bitmap at position x, y, using the specified font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter can be 0 or one of the following flags:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_LEFT - Draw the text left-aligned (same as 0).\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_CENTRE - Draw the text centered around the given position.\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_RIGHT - Draw the text right-aligned to the given position.\\nIt can also be combined with this flag:\\n\\nALLEGRO_ALIGN_INTEGER - Always draw text aligned to an integer pixel position. This was formerly the default behaviour. Since: 5.0.8, 5.1.4\\nThis function does not support newline characters (\\\\n), but you can use al_draw_multiline_text for multi line text output.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317627.010200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'daab2755-7989-4973-81db-adf0be063491',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"what's next, to draw text once I have loaded the font?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317575.010000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'aaf9ee52-2304-4f3e-8ad9-07adde246b00',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here's some information on al_load_ttf_font:\\n\\nALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_ttf_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)\\n\\nLoads a TrueType font from a file using the FreeType library. Quoting from the FreeType FAQ this means support for many different font formats:\\n\\nTrueType, OpenType, Type1, CID, CFF, Windows FON/FNT, X11 PCF, and others\\n\\nThe size parameter determines the size the font will be rendered at, specified in pixels. The standard font size is measured in units per EM, if you instead want to specify the size as the total height of glyphs in pixels, pass it as a negative value.\\n\\nNote: If you want to display text at multiple sizes, load the font multiple times with different size parameters.\\n\\nThe following flags are supported:\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_KERNING - Do not use any kerning even if the font file supports it.\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_MONOCHROME - Load as a monochrome font (which means no anti-aliasing of the font is done).\\n\\nALLEGRO_TTF_NO_AUTOHINT - Disable the Auto Hinter which is enabled by default in newer versions of FreeType. Since: 5.0.6, 5.1.2\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317399.009500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e36f91fc-e208-4121-95cc-25c1836b6536',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you use al_load_ttf_font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317345.009300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '180e8c47-09f1-49c3-8661-03bc68137148',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to use al_load_font to load a font:\\n\\nALLEGRO_FONT *al_load_font(char const *filename, int size, int flags)\\n\\nLoads a font from disk. This will use al_load_bitmap_font_flags if you pass the name of a known bitmap format, or else al_load_ttf_font.\\n\\nThe flags parameter is passed through to either of those functions. Bitmap and TTF fonts are also affected by the current bitmap flags at the time the font is loaded.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317296.009000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0a25f12f-b79a-4ebb-a1f0-c4f3495346c2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"what's next?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317249.008800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '75bc6907-e450-459b-82e8-04e5d6dee689',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to start with al_init_font_addon:\\n\\nbool al_init_font_addon(void)\\n\\nInitialise the font addon.\\n\\nNote that if you intend to load bitmap fonts, you will need to initialise allegro_image separately (unless you are using another library to load images).\\n\\nSimilarly, if you wish to load truetype-fonts, do not forget to also call al_init_ttf_addon.\\n\\nReturns true on success, false on failure. On the 5.0 branch, this function has no return value. You may wish to avoid checking the return value if your code needs to be compatible with Allegro 5.0. Currently, the function will never return false.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547317070.008300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f31522f8-6b2c-43cd-9556-7aa1417010ff',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you draw text with Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316992.008100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2fab2125-dcf8-4aa2-b70b-4a9ac0a9f80f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Great!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316927.007800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '31fc3b26-dcc3-4228-814f-50fd057a50d1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ok, it works',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316916.007600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '66f3696d-aa5a-4f12-a7cf-435a9dd6c2eb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Have you called al_init_acodec_addon?\\n\\nbool al_init_acodec_addon(void)\\n\\nThis function registers all the known audio file type handlers for al_load_sample, al_save_sample, al_load_audio_stream, etc.\\n\\nDepending on what libraries are available, the full set of recognised extensions is: .wav, .flac, .ogg, .opus, .it, .mod, .s3m, .xm, .voc.\\n\\nLimitations:\\n\\nSaving is only supported for wav files.\\n\\nThe wav file loader currently only supports 8/16 bit little endian PCM files. 16 bits are used when saving wav files. Use flac files if more precision is required.\\n\\nModule files (.it, .mod, .s3m, .xm) are often composed with streaming in mind, and sometimes cannot be easily rendered into a finite length sample. Therefore they cannot be loaded with al_load_sample/al_load_sample_f and must be streamed with al_load_audio_stream or al_load_audio_stream_f.\\n\\n.voc file streaming is unimplemented.\\n\\nReturn true on success.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316355.007400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c294622a-2d71-4369-b7c2-5aec4dc8fd7c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you use allegro_acodec to handle .wav audio files?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316321.007200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5b77aa7a-9762-4e5b-b32e-37dcce8abbdd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you get the error message when al_load_sample fails?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547316231.006500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '959f5c91-4f4b-4535-b20e-83bcf305dfbe',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to use al_load_sample followed by al_play_sample:\\n\\nALLEGRO_SAMPLE *al_load_sample(const char *filename)\\n\\nLoads a few different audio file formats based on their extension.\\n\\nNote that this stores the entire file in memory at once, which may be time consuming. To read the file as it is needed, use al_load_audio_stream.\\n\\nReturns the sample on success, NULL on failure.\\n\\nNote: the allegro_audio library does not support any audio file formats by default. You must use the allegro_acodec addon, or register your own format handler.\\n\\nbool al_play_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl, float gain, float pan, float speed,\\n   ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE loop, ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID *ret_id)\\n\\nPlays a sample on one of the sample instances created by al_reserve_samples. Returns true on success, false on failure. Playback may fail because all the reserved sample instances are currently used.\\n\\nParameters:\\n\\ngain - relative volume at which the sample is played; 1.0 is normal.\\npan - 0.0 is centred, -1.0 is left, 1.0 is right, or ALLEGRO_AUDIO_PAN_NONE.\\nspeed - relative speed at which the sample is played; 1.0 is normal.\\nloop - ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_ONCE, ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP, or ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_BIDIR\\nret_id - if non-NULL the variable which this points to will be assigned an id representing the sample being played. If al_play_sample returns false, then the contents of ret_id are invalid and must not be used as argument to other functions.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315886.006200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '68f00f38-651d-479b-bfdc-04e29e7e89f3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you play a single wav file in Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315791.006000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e3c11a31-3541-44cd-aecf-18edb632e277',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here's some information on al_reserve_samples:\\n\\nbool al_reserve_samples(int reserve_samples)\\n\\nReserves a number of sample instances, attaching them to the default mixer. If no default mixer is set when this function is called, then it will create one and attach it to the default voice. If no default voice has been set, it, too, will be created.\\n\\nIf you call this function a second time with a smaller number of samples, then the excess internal sample instances will be destroyed causing some sounds to stop and some instances returned by al_lock_sample_id to be invalidated.\\n\\nThis diagram illustrates the structures that are set up:\\n\\n                                      sample instance 1\\n                                    / sample instance 2\\ndefault voice &lt;-- default mixer &lt;---         .\\n                                    \\\\        .\\n                                      sample instance N\\nReturns true on success, false on error. al_install_audio must have been called first.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315702.005600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f78c3a76-f02d-4a8b-9028-1244e353bc42',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'describe al_reserve_samples',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315651.005400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ce073ca8-476b-4623-9a27-c748fdd11ec3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to start with al_install_audio:\\n\\nbool al_install_audio(void)\\n\\nInstall the audio subsystem.\\n\\nReturns true on success, false on failure.\\n\\nNote: most users will call al_reserve_samples and al_init_acodec_addon after this.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315580.005100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e544a472-8636-4436-996e-eedf2ec4b398',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you play sounds in Allegro',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315522.004900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ce3bb7f7-fc0d-499c-9921-5a820f07d673',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Great!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315502.004600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '18260126-6edd-4171-8c6d-ce94884004c0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'great, it works',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547315474.004400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c852fc3e-7aea-4fb6-a403-25cc81a24ee4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You can retrieve the keyboard state with al_get_keyboard_state:\\n\\nvoid al_get_keyboard_state(ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE *ret_state)\\n\\nSave the state of the keyboard specified at the time the function is called into the structure pointed to by ret_state.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314974.004200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0e3aabe4-d8b9-4f80-9a54-fbd83e5cf2be',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you retrieve the current ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE for the keyboard?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314956.004000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '24a80be3-412f-4292-a9c0-485a4e3c830e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What would you like to do with it? Here\\'s some basic information:\\n\\nALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE\\n\\ntypedef struct ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE;\\n\\nThis is a structure that is used to hold a \"snapshot\" of a keyboard\\'s state at a particular instant. It contains the following publically readable fields:\\n\\ndisplay - points to the display that had keyboard focus at the time the state was saved. If no display was focused, this points to NULL.\\nYou cannot read the state of keys directly. Use the function al_key_down.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314847.003500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c97d8038-f9e6-4587-ba31-cda4fd15b04f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you use ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE ?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314772.003300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '00a348ed-f43a-44cb-8d9c-6aaf43ed7325',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You can check that with al_key_down:\\n\\nbool al_key_down(const ALLEGRO_KEYBOARD_STATE *state, int keycode)\\n\\nReturn true if the key specified was held down in the state specified.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314715.002900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e26e2f84-4d15-4a32-9d55-009676329621',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you check key pressed state',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314667.002700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6584ac7e-73d4-4239-b1b1-26c148e57d0c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You'll probably want to use al_get_keyboard_event_source:\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_SOURCE *al_get_keyboard_event_source(void)\\n\\nRetrieve the keyboard event source. All keyboard events are generated by this event source.\\n\\nReturns NULL if the keyboard subsystem was not installed.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314589.002300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '9adc0c89-2e10-4cf3-a711-06d944c4741e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do you handle keyboard events?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314508.002100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0b856b64-642e-4907-93aa-4838a8932c9a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You\\'ll probably want to look at one of the following events:\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_DOWN\\n\\nA keyboard key was pressed.\\n\\nkeyboard.keycode (int)\\nThe code corresponding to the physical key which was pressed. See the Key codes section for the list of ALLEGRO_KEY_* constants.\\nkeyboard.display (ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *)\\nThe display which had keyboard focus when the event occurred.\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_UP\\n\\nA keyboard key was released.\\n\\nkeyboard.keycode (int)\\nThe code corresponding to the physical key which was released. See the Key codes section for the list of ALLEGRO_KEY_* constants.\\nkeyboard.display (ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *)\\nThe display which had keyboard focus when the event occurred.\\n\\nALLEGRO_EVENT_KEY_CHAR\\n\\nA character was typed on the keyboard, or a character was auto-repeated.\\n\\nkeyboard.keycode (int)\\nThe code corresponding to the physical key which was last pressed. See the Key codes section for the list of ALLEGRO_KEY_* constants.\\nkeyboard.unichar (int)\\nA Unicode code point (character). This may be zero or negative if the event was generated for a non-visible \"character\", such as an arrow or Function key. In that case you can act upon the keycode field.\\n\\nSome special keys will set the unichar field to their standard ASCII values: Tab=9, Return=13, Escape=27. In addition if you press the Control key together with A to Z the unichar field will have the values 1 to 26. For example Ctrl-A will set unichar to 1 and Ctrl-H will set it to 8.\\n\\nAs of Allegro 5.0.2 there are some inconsistencies in the treatment of Backspace (8 or 127) and Delete (127 or 0) keys on different platforms. These can be worked around by checking the keycode field.\\n\\nkeyboard.modifiers (unsigned)\\nThis is a bitfield of the modifier keys which were pressed when the event occurred. See \"Keyboard modifier flags\" for the constants.\\nkeyboard.repeat (bool)\\nIndicates if this is a repeated character.\\nkeyboard.display (ALLEGRO_DISPLAY *)\\nThe display which had keyboard focus when the event occurred.\\nNote: in many input methods, characters are not entered one-for-one with physical key presses. Multiple key presses can combine to generate a single character, e.g. apostrophe + e may produce \\'é\\'. Fewer key presses can also generate more characters, e.g. macro sequences expanding to common phrases.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314247.001900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'eab18df0-e8d1-4424-8a79-7de25083c370',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"what's next?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547314206.001700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ac862d87-adf2-44ee-bcdb-d0cc1a936d65',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"To get started, you'll probably want to use al_install_keyboard:\\n\\nbool al_install_keyboard(void)\\n\\nInstall a keyboard driver. Returns true if successful. If a driver was already installed, nothing happens and true is returned.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547313961.001500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4632f4b5-701a-4e37-a684-de8ba79e2779',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How do you handle keyboard input in Allegro?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547313888.001300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ec739eaa-f793-48e1-a87a-0e986464efd0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'very well!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547312687.001000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0720f4e9-076e-438b-8256-c3c915d74f7d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I'm good, how about you?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547312654.000800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0b30e502-964e-4281-85f4-6d817cb426ed',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How are you?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547312619.000600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd9c2258d-0d0c-4ffb-9b81-c4b4238bdafa',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hello!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547312591.000400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fa49d845-0dfb-415c-88f5-048db401b857',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'hello',\n",
       "     'user': 'UFCAHB2NN',\n",
       "     'ts': '1547312573.000200'}],\n",
       "   'has_more': False}},\n",
       " 30: {'library': 'allegro',\n",
       "  'metadata': {'wizard': '02', 'programmer': '30'},\n",
       "  'score': {0: 1, 1: 2, 2: 1, 3: 0, 4: 0, 5: 0, 6: 0},\n",
       "  'entry': {0: 'English',\n",
       "   1: 'Secondary school',\n",
       "   2: '4',\n",
       "   3: '1',\n",
       "   4: 'No',\n",
       "   5: 'No',\n",
       "   6: '',\n",
       "   7: 'Novice'},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 5, 1: 5, 2: 4, 3: 4, 4: 4, 5: 5, 6: 3, 7: 3, 8: 4},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': 'bbea6f8a-6f2b-46bf-ae7f-596193cc5387',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I am unsure, please specify',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552257030.023100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '70282d9c-9267-42f3-9e98-da44998fc65e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'My al_draw_text is not drawing',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552257003.022900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e6be7ec0-b913-4b11-9b9a-47ac926c203d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'One such utility is:\\n\\nALLEGRO_COLOR al_map_rgb(float r, float g, float b)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256933.022600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '63b3ff16-025d-4b1b-a105-3623bd7a7483',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you show my the utility functions?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256888.022400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e125efa6-0e0f-473c-9ea7-e0e36b8edd27',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'rgb are typically within [0,255]. Allegro5 supports utility functions to map rbg values to an ALLEGRO_COLOR struct instance',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256831.021900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'dea83537-440c-4e04-96fd-c3f4622f28bb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How big are the numbers r, g, b, and a typically are for ALLEGRO_COLOR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256782.021700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '73e84576-9532-4a35-bda0-7a2dd6e1915f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'It depends on your screen. I would suggest trying a bunch of values. Typically, I would suggest 72',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256749.021300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3a32522a-dbb2-43a3-8649-d961cd0cc017',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What is a typical font size for ALLEGRO_FONT',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256691.021100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd762798d-2ebc-4529-8161-449f675e2b3a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The `flags` parameter can be 0 or one of the following flags:\\n\\n- ALLEGRO_ALIGN_LEFT - Draw the text left-aligned (same as 0).\\n- ALLEGRO_ALIGN_CENTRE - Draw the text centered around the given position.\\n- ALLEGRO_ALIGN_RIGHT - Draw the text right-aligned to the given position.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256492.020800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c3dcfc12-0571-4fac-8893-803aa11c90e5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you give more more information about the flags parameter?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256377.020600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b1d8f67e-b87a-425c-8f29-96233f8ed702',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': '* Type: ALLEGRO_COLOR\\n */\\ntypedef struct ALLEGRO_COLOR ALLEGRO_COLOR;\\n\\nstruct ALLEGRO_COLOR\\n{\\n   float r, g, b, a;\\n};',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256334.020300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f01cf781-674a-498a-bbe7-b81b86af11f3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Yes',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256250.020100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0883f9ad-61c5-49dc-8aad-dc876c4abb55',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ALLEGRO_COLOR is a struct containing rgba values. Would you like the declaration',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256196.019900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5db90604-5aab-4ae7-92bb-4f7b890eee24',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you give me more information about the color parameter',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256133.019700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8406f1d8-014e-429d-9f3a-89b7e61f14c5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You can draw text using the following function:\\n\\nvoid al_draw_text(const ALLEGRO_FONT *font,\\n   ALLEGRO_COLOR color, float x, float y, int flags,\\n   char const *text)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552256039.019400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b3786d82-071a-4fc9-9293-2d004a6161e2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Then?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255914.019200'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c59eda4c-2c5c-4550-aa55-b3d6b05337b5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is flag information:\\n\\nThe following flags are supported:\\n\\n* ALLEGRO_TTF_NO_KERNING - Do not use any kerning even if the font file\\n  supports it.\\n\\n* ALLEGRO_TTF_MONOCHROME - Load as a monochrome font (which means no\\n  anti-aliasing of the font is done).\\n\\n* ALLEGRO_TTF_NO_AUTOHINT - Disable the Auto Hinter which is enabled by default\\n  in newer versions of FreeType. Since: 5.0.6, 5.1.2',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255816.019000'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6aa093dd-e5a4-4627-9fb8-37b4b3598f90',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you elaborate on the flags parameter?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255754.018800'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '72fbe6ee-0fb6-4781-a7d2-8d2c4a3ea24f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'you can first load in a font using the function:\\n\\nALLEGRO_FONT* al_load_ttf_font(const char* fpath, int size, int flags);',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255741.018500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '899b3e6d-fdcd-4379-bac4-843d2d67206a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Yes',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255685.018300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '9aa989dd-c0d5-45e0-a7af-9e306f37beb1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Have you created a display?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255680.018100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bc13d5bb-3663-47d1-94b9-707f7dfb2bb0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Then?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255656.017900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a7e82992-b0ae-4390-9a41-82008c2e0a94',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Great! You can start by initializing fonts. This can be done via the functions:\\n\\nbool al_init_font_addon(void);\\nbool al_init_ttf_addon(void);',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255613.017700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fda3ba78-93ae-423b-bfae-9f9b085a2d9f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Yes',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255570.017500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '36d30286-04d7-494b-a76a-2ce9e9a4a56b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Would you like to draw a font?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255567.017300'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '369608af-657c-448b-bc0c-5575fbb7dc3c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I would like to display a score on the corner of the screen',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255546.017100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5de71ee8-0d9d-4874-9879-415af4b7c345',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I am sorry, there are multiple ways to show text, specifically to which do you refer?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255515.016700'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5f5610ab-0c9a-4f6a-9dd1-88375682d7a0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'How would I display text?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255472.016500'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bef123ef-5ac7-4d4c-a5f5-3afbd7d942a4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here are the options for ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE:\\n\\nSample and stream playback mode.\\n\\n* ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_ONCE\\n* ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_LOOP\\n* ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE_BIDIR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255331.016100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3c5c7d32-d6a9-48a9-b7d6-a10ef64567b7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'And you explain more about ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255301.015900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ce898adf-6804-401b-bf21-9656e9cadea5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure! Here is a description of the parameters:\\n\\nALLEGRO_SAMPLE* spl:        The sample file data\\nfloat gain:                 The gain of the played sample\\nfloat pan:                  The pan of the played sample\\nfloat speed:                The speed to play the file\\nALLEGRO_PLAYMODE loop:      whether to loop the file or not\\nALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID* ret_id:  Typically NULL, however this is the return id to be used',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255261.015600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0a36fb1f-c8c1-473b-936c-dba8829193ea',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Can you explain to me the parameters of that function?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255136.015400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fa65aeeb-d555-4536-ab88-3ee1e82e2845',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The next step is to play the loaded ALLEGRO_SAMPLE* object using the function:\\n\\nbool al_play_sample(ALLEGRO_SAMPLE *spl, float gain, float pan, float speed,\\n   ALLEGRO_PLAYMODE loop, ALLEGRO_SAMPLE_ID *ret_id)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552255083.015100'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '542cc681-0920-4dc7-9b22-26e529377392',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Okay, what's the next step?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UGTTQM082',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552254974.014900'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6758f5d4-3aeb-46b3-8ca1-0cfd98205646',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'int num_samples in reference to function:\\n\\nbool al_reserve_samples(int num_samples)\\n\\nrefers to the number of sound files you want to load into memory.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1552254938.014600'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '087e8b9a-3d80-4ea4-bb9d-a6c0a0ed9987',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
