       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'tell me the easiest one',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB6TBU716',\n",
       "     'ts': '1528989593.000969'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ec1daf33-2538-44bf-9171-fa3631fbc7c5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are several functions to authenticate a session, would you like me to enumerate them all?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1528989571.000539'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'efc23638-1a65-4f32-aead-e5b94ab26ce7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'You can set properties of a session using the \"ssh_options_set(session, option, char*)\" function. An example would be to set the host options, which can be done with the following statement \"ssh_options_set(my_ssh_session, SSH_OPTIONS_HOST, \"129.0.0.1\");\"',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
