       "   7: 2,\n",
       "   8: 2,\n",
       "   9: 2,\n",
       "   10: 2,\n",
       "   11: 2,\n",
       "   12: 2},\n",
       "  'entry': {0: '>19',\n",
       "   1: '>10',\n",
       "   2: 'Yes',\n",
       "   3: 'Used it briefly.',\n",
       "   4: 'Intermediate'},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 3, 1: 5, 2: 3, 3: 4, 4: 4, 5: 4, 6: 4, 7: 5, 8: 3},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': '3b178d90-5df3-4674-a09e-017ad1cb4de3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is an example:\\n\\nsftp_file file;\\nsftp_session sftp;\\nint access_type = O_WRONLY | O_CREAT | O_TRUNC;\\n\\nfile = sftp_open(sftp, \"helloworld/helloworld.txt\",  access_type, S_IRWXU);',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110768.000365'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '148a376f-79da-4241-ba47-70283e754708',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"sftp_file sftp_open\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tfile,\\nint \\taccesstype,\\nmode_t \\tmode \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a file on the server.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The sftp session handle.\\nfile: The file to be opened.\\naccesstype: Is one of O_RDONLY, O_WRONLY or O_RDWR which request opening the file read-only,write-only or read/write. Acesss may also be bitwise-or'd with one or more of the following: O_CREAT - If the file does not exist it will be created. O_EXCL - When used with O_CREAT, if the file already exists it is an error and the open will fail. O_TRUNC - If the file already exists it will be truncated.\\nmode: Mode specifies the permissions to use if a new file is created. It is modified by the process's umask in the usual way: The permissions of the created file are (mode &amp; ~umask)\\n\\nReturns\\nA sftp file handle, NULL on error with ssh and sftp error set.\\n\\nReferences ssh_buffer_free(), ssh_buffer_new(), and ssh_string_from_char().\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_get_error()\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110761.000248'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '723fac38-7769-4baa-9f07-32707651b70c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you give me an example of sftp_open',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110672.000093'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1df13d14-1956-4e3f-84df-7a10d47d4ad1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'tell me about sftp_open',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110663.000392'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ffa5e554-3f2c-4a8c-b2b2-a5a7bae0e717',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I can\\'t find specific information on \"server responses\" but in context, I believe you are referring to \\n\\n/* Error return codes */\\n #define SSH_OK 0     /* No error */\\n #define SSH_ERROR -1 /* Error of some kind */\\n #define SSH_AGAIN -2 /* The nonblocking call must be repeated */\\n #define SSH_EOF -127 /* We have already a eof */',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110629.000060'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fbc50009-82c7-4a13-b422-bf41c47a885c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'tell me about server respones',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110409.000350'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7811b26b-69f5-430d-a9d9-c2609d67c2a7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'int sftp_get_error\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nGet the last sftp error.\\nUse this function to get the latest error set by a posix like sftp function.\\n\\nParameters\\nsftp: The sftp session where the error is saved.\\n\\nReturns\\nThe saved error (see server responses), &lt; 0 if an error in the function occured.\\n\\nReferences ssh_buffer_free(), and ssh_buffer_new().\\n\\nSee also\\nServer responses',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110372.000079'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e77fa196-0dca-4e04-a2b1-5728e7376131',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'tell me about sftp_get_error',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110350.000445'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '62370cb8-0dfb-47cf-8023-4c7d4f43dd71',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I can't find a function that checks if a directory exists. However, there are many functions requiring a directory, including \\n\\nsftp_dir sftp_opendir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tpath \\n)\\n\\nsftp_attributes sftp_readdir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsession,\\nsftp_dir \\tdir \\n)\\n\\nint sftp_rmdir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp,\\nconst char * \\tdirectory \\n)\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110329.000102'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '85d854d5-e301-4b03-b972-7dc44cc9108c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'tell me about Error',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110329.000087'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'abe2182e-1431-453d-8f1d-3591b3375844',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Was sftp_write useful in creating a file? If not, sftp_open might help.\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a file on the server.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110221.000141'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '040883b1-6bd6-44fe-82a2-d88629bc4d56',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I tell if a directory already exists',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110154.000004'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7a753031-f5b2-458d-b61c-a3fbbb208dac',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a file in libssh using sftp',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110139.000211'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b0c6badc-4025-46a8-87aa-215d2d5172f0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\n0 on success, &lt; 0 on error with ssh and sftp error set.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110065.000224'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3777f982-29d6-4303-9df6-096af5da12c7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what does sftp_mkdir returhn',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532110052.000057'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e7b7b387-cc1b-4076-a491-24be97fbeac3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure, here\\'s an example:\\n\\nint rc;\\nsftp_session sftp;\\nrc = sftp_mkdir(sftp, \"helloworld\", S_IRWXU);',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109584.000188'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'da8d3b4d-bc7b-4d6b-807b-fc1b0b49cb75',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you give me an example of sftp_mkdir',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109502.000320'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'cd24a0bc-f80c-4644-b73a-1c8380a8e51a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I can\\'t find a function to \"create\" a file, but I found one to \"write\" a file:\\n\\nssize_t sftp_write\\t(\\tsftp_file file, \\nconst void * buf, \\nsize_t count \\n)\\n\\nDescription \\nWrite to a file using an opened sftp file handle.\\n\\nParameters \\nfile: Open sftp file handle to write to. \\nbuf: Pointer to buffer to write data. \\ncount: Size of buffer in bytes.\\n\\nReturns \\nNumber of bytes written, &lt; 0 on error with ssh and sftp error set.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109448.000138'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b4a0a951-e091-461b-8303-b9b8921c9005',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found two functions that may be appropriate to create a directory:\\n\\nint sftp_mkdir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp,\\nconst char * \\tdirectory,\\nmode_t \\tmode \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nCreate a directory.\\n\\nand\\n\\nsftp_dir sftp_opendir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tpath \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a directory used to obtain directory entries.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109384.000460'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '60e4d439-24d4-42ac-b974-6d95142a64a9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a file in libssh using sftp',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109376.000348'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '086900b9-014f-4ff4-8a9f-1e5b8acd5d31',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a directory in libssh using sftp',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109363.000482'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '94d0d74d-9291-4fbe-acd5-82541eddacaa',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This should do it:\\n\\nint sftp_init\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nInitialize the sftp session with the server.\\n\\nParameters\\nsftp: The sftp session to initialize.\\n\\nReturns\\n0 on success, &lt; 0 on error with ssh error set.\\n\\nReferences ssh_buffer_new().\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_new()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109308.000052'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'af94e9cf-030e-402d-9bfd-b7f27e92b7c3',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a directory',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109300.000373'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4c6ce7fe-ce06-4d39-afe4-ecc54cf6cdc8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I init the sftp session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109280.000452'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a3ba8f2d-dabb-4c2a-98da-e5fe669ccb8a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sftp_session sftp_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nStart a new sftp session.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA new sftp session or NULL on error.\\n\\nReferences ssh_channel_free(), ssh_channel_new(), and ssh_channel_open_session().\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_free()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109196.000454'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e6298fd4-0b99-45fd-95ad-fdc15284047f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a sftp session in libssh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109149.000494'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd5c23727-6414-4515-8889-8004a231a6ad',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function should let you open a channel session\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_session\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a session channel (suited for a shell, not TCP forwarding).\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: An allocated channel.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_open_forward()\\nssh_channel_request_env()\\nssh_channel_request_shell()\\nssh_channel_request_exec()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532109017.000462'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd48bcdda-2514-42f8-bb23-6756a85c8ae4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function may help with deciphering a disconnect message\\n\\nconst char* ssh_get_disconnect_message\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108921.000160'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '577011bf-882f-4023-bb36-80730bcfbb55',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I open a channel session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108917.000202'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '72c360ee-c3fa-4f5b-9064-bf3934e0d01c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I don't have the channel open\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108883.000356'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6e694c96-95bd-4a17-a258-7e2975995e0f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'oh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108880.000183'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'de0c6bb3-8eb8-4c95-b9e5-72fa3c773dae',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what does ssh_msg_disconnect mean',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108788.000373'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '75400d35-8dc0-4ac5-b397-36490c7cf2b5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function may help you debug: \\n\\nconst char* ssh_get_error\\t(\\tvoid * \\terror\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nRetrieve the error text message from the last error.\\n\\nParameters\\nerror: An ssh_session or ssh_bind.\\n\\nReturns\\nA static string describing the error.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108683.000029'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'eeceae88-6427-4e9b-a0d4-71c112b35fb6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'SSH_ERROR',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108641.000400'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ba8f075d-b1cb-4543-a5ed-a1de084d5219',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'What kind of error are you getting?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108635.000265'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5ccd7f6b-6c12-4d52-b023-6eed9e683054',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'why am I getting an error on ssh_channel_request_exec',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108582.000282'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'cf2adf79-db93-4e95-b1d2-b2a947f7d644',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108086.000084'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8d6c7c06-117a-4b7e-a431-8ea9fedd5be0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what does ssh_channel_close     return',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108070.000440'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'da0a5388-78ef-470e-aef5-31a34ef6d8a5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I think you can use int ssh_channel_close\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108041.000468'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '35f9c257-113d-40b8-8707-d497236f36ca',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I close the channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532108010.000398'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fb3f9c48-1f71-4c8d-ad93-09db3846529b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"This method should work:\\n\\nint ssh_channel_send_eof\\t(\\tssh_channel channel\\t)\\n\\nDescription \\nSend an end of file on the channel. \\nThis doesn't close the channel. You may still read from it but not write.\\n\\nParameters \\nchannel: The channel to send the eof to.\\n\\nReturns \\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107990.000329'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2e848344-05af-4908-9f33-5bf58a102ebb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I send an eof to the channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107961.000111'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4c048deb-2e0a-47a8-9242-16ac73f3ba80',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Sure, here's an example:\\nssh_channel channel;\\nchar buffer[256];\\nint nbytes;\\nnbytes = ssh_channel_read(channel, buffer, sizeof(buffer), 0);\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107908.000083'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '090e7513-6cad-40a3-8d07-da64f19d3a6a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you give me an example of ssh_channel_read',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107789.000121'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a353e5fa-f1a0-4780-ac29-abe5a515d115',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found a couple of functions that involve reading from the channel:\\n\\nint channel_read_buffer\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nssh_buffer \\tbuffer,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_read\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nvoid * \\tdest,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_read_nonblocking\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nvoid * \\tdest,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_read_timeout\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nvoid * \\tdest,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr,\\nint \\ttimeout \\n)\\n\\nWould you like to hear more about one of these?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107760.000320'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '09521349-39fc-4c53-a15c-f6063d2ccec6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I read the result of ssh_channel_request_exec',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107681.000079'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '23b52c51-7558-4543-ab2d-6b240d024a28',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107629.000328'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bb2cc57c-b810-44b2-a720-5d58480483ef',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what does ssh_channel_request_exec     return',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107610.000413'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '812423fc-679f-4699-8a2c-05381d549bd1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"int ssh_channel_request_exec\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\tcmd \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nRun a shell command without an interactive shell.\\nThis is similar to 'sh -c command'.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107588.000435'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1d11a92c-5eae-4468-b9bf-e1498ed470bc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I execute a command with a ssh_channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107551.000307'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '56f0842a-0bba-43e5-af5b-10f522f32000',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I think you're looking for \\n\\nssh_channel ssh_channel_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nAllocate a new channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA pointer to a newly allocated channel, NULL on error.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107467.000360'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '02898de9-3c0e-4a25-bab8-423fa908799c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a new ssh_channel  with libssh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532107428.000466'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'af75a727-2f3a-4b37-9092-11905665fc0e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\nSSH_SERVER_KNOWN_OK: The server is known and has not changed.\\nSSH_SERVER_KNOWN_CHANGED: The server key has changed. Either you are under attack or the administrator changed the key. You HAVE to warn the user about a possible attack.\\nSSH_SERVER_FOUND_OTHER: The server gave use a key of a type while we had an other type recorded. It is a possible attack.\\nSSH_SERVER_NOT_KNOWN: The server is unknown. User should confirm the MD5 is correct.\\nSSH_SERVER_FILE_NOT_FOUND: The known host file does not exist. The host is thus unknown. File will be created if host key is accepted.\\nSSH_SERVER_ERROR: Some error happened.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106890.000334'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c6116f69-30b5-45b5-a003-3d8ca7d86702',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what does ssh_is_server_known   return',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106882.000029'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'aacd2203-2d65-40de-b5e2-99d352cc6bf0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"There is a function int ssh_is_server_known\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nCheck if the server is known.\\nChecks the user's known host file for a previous connection to the current server.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106857.000094'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e0e0f07f-ba8d-4651-8513-7851635c0c4d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I check that the host is known in libssh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106809.000339'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a2873ac6-454d-4ca7-9d7a-1ebf5d83d6cd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Returns\\nSSH_AUTH_ERROR: A serious error happened.\\nSSH_AUTH_DENIED: Authentication failed: use another method\\nSSH_AUTH_PARTIAL: You've been partially authenticated, you still have to use another method\\nSSH_AUTH_SUCCESS: Authentication success\\nSSH_AUTH_AGAIN: In nonblocking mode, you've got to call this again later.\\nNote\\nMost server implementations do not permit changing the username during authentication. The username should only be set with ssh_options_set() only before you connect to the server.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106688.000373'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'efb7218c-48b6-47b2-b29a-290bf79cf076',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what are the return values for ssh_userauth_password',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106658.000194'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5f19dd22-e3ae-41a8-853b-8e0fa49458d4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR on error.\\nSSH_AGAIN, if the session is in nonblocking mode, and call must be done again.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106595.000089'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2cff14ad-cdf3-4cfc-828e-34d276835c37',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what are the return values for ssh_connect',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106587.000135'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b80ec5c9-d924-4fa2-9ab3-c9d8dc2af18e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what do the return values for ssh_connect',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106579.000433'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '688cb789-1c2d-4c9e-9d6f-2abe70a05212',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'To connect, I would recommend the function\\n int ssh_connect\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t).\\n\\nI also found a reference to \"localhost\" in \\nint ssh_options_getopt\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nint * \\targcptr,\\nchar ** \\targv \\n)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106501.000377'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '397ef56a-3ad5-461e-b446-22d71d68b42b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I connect to localhost with libssh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106384.000350'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'faee7e24-a22e-4c6a-ba04-6bbf80b16f35',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found a few functions that authenticate with username:\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_none\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tusername \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_password\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tusername,\\nconst char * \\tpassword \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_publickey\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tusername,\\nconst ssh_key \\tprivkey \\n)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106375.000239'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '935751b4-7195-47d7-9adf-a37a44c3f45e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'username',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106321.000236'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7a68bc28-f7a2-481b-a57e-0e42a7b416bd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are several authentication functions. How would you like to authenticate?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106313.000205'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e0cdfa11-1c13-4918-a33f-6983b9d84acf',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I authenticate my libssh session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106229.000147'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '905e688d-603d-4311-b7b2-330cd95295c7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I'm glad to hear it!\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106214.000322'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8709549e-dd30-488f-97c0-76a9bcfc0437',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sweet',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106191.000053'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1570cd96-afd3-4301-ab1c-c399d3279a0e',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure! Something like:\\n\\nmy_ssh_session = ssh_new();',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106188.000075'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ec90af73-03ae-4f5c-9d19-f7f6d30bb47c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you give me an example on how to use ssh_new',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106169.000308'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '65da6bc2-abea-459f-a735-0b7af00a07ea',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I would suggest using the function ssh_new:\\n\\nssh_session ssh_new\\t(\\tvoid \\t\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nCreate a new ssh session.\\n\\nReturns\\nA new ssh_session pointer, NULL on error.\\n\\nReferences ssh_buffer_new(), and ssh_set_blocking().',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106152.000279'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '26c205ae-52b2-494d-b36d-e5177136781d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a new session in libssh',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106122.000268'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1b91e661-4f27-4589-a047-9aa89e23bcce',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hello! I am Apiza, an automated virtual assistant for programmers that is supervised by a human. I look forward to helping you today!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106108.000418'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '56f885a8-f5b8-4805-97f3-5af4e491f991',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hi',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBVAD029M',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532106086.000450'}],\n",
       "   'has_more': False}},\n",
       " 6: {'library': 'libssh',\n",
       "  'metadata': {'wizard': '01', 'programmer': '06'},\n",
       "  'score': {0: 2,\n",
       "   1: 2,\n",
       "   2: 1,\n",
       "   3: 2,\n",
       "   4: 2,\n",
       "   5: 2,\n",
       "   6: 2,\n",
       "   7: 1,\n",
       "   8: 1,\n",
       "   9: 0,\n",
       "   10: 0,\n",
       "   11: 0,\n",
       "   12: 0},\n",
       "  'entry': {0: '2-10', 1: '2-10', 2: 'No', 3: '', 4: 'Novice'},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 5, 1: 4, 2: 4, 3: 4, 4: 4, 5: 4, 6: 4, 7: 3, 8: 2},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': 'f547394a-364a-4153-ab28-b82c6f841ff4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'It looks like you do. You can use\\n\\n int sftp_init\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp\\t)\\nReturns\\n0 on success, &lt; 0 on error with ssh error set.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282847.000003'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3936a541-3825-44ed-807e-f69b9f0464cf',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'do I need to call any methods to initialize the sftp_session?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282811.000035'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'abfdaeaf-e939-4998-b4d6-40aad9ce5da2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sftp_session sftp_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nStart a new sftp session.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA new sftp session or NULL on error.\\n\\nReferences ssh_channel_free(), ssh_channel_new(), and ssh_channel_open_session().\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_free()',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282677.000040'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ab4e23fa-436f-49c7-9aa5-2ef7a7463e41',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I create a new sftp_session on an existing ssh_session?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282641.000064'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c836a4e1-79c0-46f6-be8a-d82b9966d21c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I am glad to hear it!',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282587.000006'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '19c5130e-8632-4bff-993c-30d3f109c093',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'nevermind I figured it out',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282574.000023'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6b60f5f7-4b6e-4642-af0c-1733b26852e5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ssh_channel_close only closes the channel. ssh_channel_free closes and frees the channel.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282569.000029'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1d7dc5e8-a798-4801-80be-886137172f89',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'does ssh_channel_close also free the channel?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282503.000015'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2cb0f520-5c50-47d2-863b-6a7a964f74d7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'To send an eof, you may use int ssh_channel_send_eof\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282153.000033'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fce3d79c-1826-490b-94aa-014faaa14afc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"One of those methods may help:\\n\\nint ssh_channel_close\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\nDescription\\nClose a channel.\\nThis sends an end of file and then closes the channel. You won't be able to recover any data the server was going to send or was in buffers.\\n\\n\\nvoid ssh_channel_free\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\nDescription\\nClose and free a channel.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282135.000051'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5d0b99d6-5893-4878-9c87-b61b5c822a59',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'specifically by sending an eof?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282099.000062'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f14e2934-2a5b-46db-9b45-ed1536c731b4',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'how do I shut down a channel?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532282081.000049'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a8066126-5fc2-4c77-9c91-0c60558f551b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The buffer variable used in ssh_channel_read is a void *\\n\\nint ssh_channel_read\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nvoid * \\tdest,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr \\n)\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to read from.\\ndest: The destination buffer which will get the data.\\ncount: The count of bytes to be read.\\nis_stderr: A boolean value to mark reading from the stderr flow.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281991.000023'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '73691818-e731-439a-85fb-b71e3dd59ead',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'just a char *?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281923.000009'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2fb06519-c588-4553-bf3d-d375db9880be',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what is buffer in that code sample?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281911.000055'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7101574a-f121-48c6-9f4c-6bf76afb7b1d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This method should work:\\n\\nint ssh_channel_request_exec\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\tcmd \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nRun a shell command without an interactive shell.\\nThis is similar to \\'sh -c command\\'.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to execute the command.\\ncmd: The command to execute (e.g. \"ls ~/ -al | grep -i reports\").\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.\\n\\nExample:\\n\\nrc = channel_request_exec(channel, \"ps aux\");\\nif (rc &gt; 0) {\\n    return -1;\\n}\\nwhile ((rc = channel_read(channel, buffer, sizeof(buffer), 0)) &gt; 0) {\\n    if (fwrite(buffer, 1, rc, stdout) != (unsigned int) rc) {\\n        return -1;\\n    }\\n}',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281717.000067'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2bb0f708-0749-4b78-9755-9b0029fafba7',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'great, and how would I execute a command on an opened channel?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281680.000007'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '59664895-db64-43c4-a1ac-05658280c7d9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure! I found the following example:\\n\\nint rc;\\nssh_channel channel;\\n...\\nrc = ssh_channel_open_session(channel);\\nif (rc != SSH_OK)\\n{\\n    ssh_channel_free(channel);\\n    return rc;\\n}',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281524.000008'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c504aa4a-4cda-486c-9411-fd738a429691',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I'm getting an SSH_ERROR.  Can you show me an example of how it's used?  Any parameters I need to set up?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281448.000025'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '91f33667-49a1-493e-a768-57bb56eb69d2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Returns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281312.000035'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b728b735-6a5a-4e40-9118-1beba8765469',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'and what are the return codes for ssh_channel_open_session?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281293.000081'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '63e25a49-7e67-4b9d-bded-8836752c1d35',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ssh_channel_open_session seems to be the more popular function.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281274.000045'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'cdd8143a-6d79-42f9-bf4e-85e0a876864f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ssh_channel_open_auth_agent:\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen an agent authentication forwarding channel.\\nThis type of channel can be opened by a server towards a client in order to provide SSH-Agent services to the server-side process. This channel can only be opened if the client claimed support by sending a channel request beforehand.\\n\\nssh_channel_open_session:\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a session channel (suited for a shell, not TCP forwarding).',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281212.000048'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '963dc5ed-3205-4f24-839a-96b75c59e03a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ok great, and whats the difference between ssh_channel_open_auth_agent and ssh_channel_open_session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281157.000038'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'aff23d28-291c-44f1-bad3-cb0d6fb72333',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure!\\n\\nssh_channel ssh_channel_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nAllocate a new channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA pointer to a newly allocated channel, NULL on error.\\n\\nReferences ssh_buffer_free(), and ssh_buffer_new().',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281100.000049'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '21267f66-9c6d-4d1c-a0ef-22cac8fc3dea',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you tell me more about ssh_channel_new().  how do I know if it executed successfully?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532281068.000033'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '413dd22d-862a-489e-bf2f-5464202c0df0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'It looks like ssh_channel ssh_channel_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t) will help create a new ssh channel. \\n\\nDescription\\nAllocate a new channel.\\n\\nThere are a few methods to open an ssh channel:\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_auth_agent\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_session\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_forward\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\tremotehost,\\nint \\tremoteport,\\nconst char * \\tsourcehost,\\nint \\tlocalport \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_reverse_forward\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\tremotehost,\\nint \\tremoteport,\\nconst char * \\tsourcehost,\\nint \\tlocalport \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_channel_open_x11\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\torig_addr,\\nint \\torig_port \\n)\\n\\nWould you like to hear more about one of these?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280984.000016'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '49745a02-969b-4360-9286-5fd17f4f7ca8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Ok, how would I create and open a new ssh channel in an existing ssh session?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280819.000047'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd898dcf1-e417-4ba4-a1c1-e9d7fdf47141',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I'm glad to hear that!\\n\\nssh_disconnect and ssh_free both return void.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280767.000051'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '3ed11a6f-0a56-462d-821e-b078ea9a7d3d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'great, that works.  And do ssh_disconnect and ssh_free return anything?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280704.000023'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '576a98b5-4c1c-4060-865f-ee518f7db5a0',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure! I found the following example:\\n\\nint rc;\\nchar * password;\\nssh_session my_ssh_session;\\n...\\nrc = ssh_userauth_password(my_ssh_session, NULL, password);\\nif (rc != SSH_AUTH_SUCCESS)\\n{\\n    fprintf(stderr, \"Error authenticating with password: %s\\\\n\",\\n            ssh_get_error(my_ssh_session));\\n    ssh_disconnect(my_ssh_session);\\n    ssh_free(my_ssh_session);\\n    exit(-1);\\n}',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280613.000056'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '559c46b0-feb4-4acb-86bb-bfb75cc264a6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'no, can you show me an example of ssh_userauth_password() being used?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280505.000075'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '570d99f0-73e1-404c-9092-9c6b5d2240cd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'A 1 denotes the enum SSH_AUTH_DENIED.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280481.000086'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '2e4f63dc-0fb0-40fe-8bdb-00a09211e2ca',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I found the following \"userauth\" methods that don\\'t need a \"username\" or \"user\"  parameter:\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_gssapi\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nconst char* ssh_userauth_kbdint_getanswer\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nunsigned int \\ti \\n)\\n\\nconst char* ssh_userauth_kbdint_getinstruction\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nconst char* ssh_userauth_kbdint_getname\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_kbdint_getnanswers\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_kbdint_getnprompts\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nconst char* ssh_userauth_kbdint_getprompt\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nunsigned int \\ti,\\nchar * \\techo \\n)\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_kbdint_setanswer\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nunsigned int \\ti,\\nconst char * \\tanswer \\n)\\n\\nWould you like to know more about any of these?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280436.000077'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '98eb8a93-4c76-4ba9-a639-11b86ee8101d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'also, what does a return code of 1 signify from ssh_userauth_password()?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280360.000014'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '60c3f35b-6a3c-4f1f-a5f0-b8bb58e4908d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'nevermind, is it possible to authenticate a user without a username?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280328.000039'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '62715800-95ad-49ed-9cc0-e427b00d073b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'I couldn\\'t find a function to \"authenticate the server\" but I found ones to \"Check if the server is known\" and \"verify [a hash of the public key]\". Would either of those be helpful?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280240.000073'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '482d2214-6481-4b1f-95b4-80510b369d8f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'what method should be used to authenticate the server?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280111.000060'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '913a2750-9b64-4538-a330-a10d7ebb7d8a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hmm, I am not certain about that. I may still be able to find an answer. Can you elaborate?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532280059.000043'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '5ec4759a-7489-4846-b903-67f57327e528',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'ok great.  What method should I use to authenticate the server?  Is it different from ssh_userauth_password() which authenticates the user?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532279869.000031'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bfafab72-9282-4aab-93d8-82784a127b74',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure thing, I was able to find one example that goes from ssh_new to ssh_connect:\\n\\n// Open session and set options\\n  my_ssh_session = ssh_new();\\n  if (my_ssh_session == NULL)\\n    exit(-1);\\n  ssh_options_set(my_ssh_session, SSH_OPTIONS_HOST, \"localhost\");\\n  // Connect to server\\n  rc = ssh_connect(my_ssh_session);',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532279522.000007'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '077fc213-912a-4505-a2fd-b0c37775e0b9',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you tell me more about how to connect to localhost after an ssh_session is successfully created?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532279425.000041'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f2089fc1-3567-498d-8105-04b9895fb77c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure!\\n\\nenum ssh_auth_e {\\n   SSH_AUTH_SUCCESS=0,\\n   SSH_AUTH_DENIED,\\n   SSH_AUTH_PARTIAL,\\n   SSH_AUTH_INFO,\\n   SSH_AUTH_AGAIN,\\n   SSH_AUTH_ERROR=-1\\n };',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532279116.000012'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1d1df2e6-85db-4d68-b4e0-e6b4a5f4a84f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'can you give me the int values for those codes?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532279052.000012'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4a79e6ca-55a4-44e7-b453-d78e0ca88462',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"You must be connected to the server before using ssh_userauth_password. \\n\\nssh_userauth_password returns\\n\\nSSH_AUTH_ERROR: A serious error happened.\\nSSH_AUTH_DENIED: Authentication failed: use another method\\nSSH_AUTH_PARTIAL: You've been partially authenticated, you still have to use another method\\nSSH_AUTH_SUCCESS: Authentication success\\nSSH_AUTH_AGAIN: In nonblocking mode, you've got to call this again later.\\nNote\\nMost server implementations do not permit changing the username during authentication. The username should only be set with ssh_options_set() only before you connect to the server.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278988.000034'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4fdd26fe-026d-47c3-a7e3-ea15de96d466',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'and for the ssh_userauth_password() method, does that only tell you if the provided authentication is valid or will it connect to the server as well?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278899.000031'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a71206b9-08a5-499b-9174-fcd2da524e5a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure it looks like these are the \"Error return codes\":\\n\\n/* Error return codes */\\n #define SSH_OK 0     /* No error */\\n #define SSH_ERROR -1 /* Error of some kind */\\n #define SSH_AGAIN -2 /* The nonblocking call must be repeated */\\n #define SSH_EOF -127 /* We have already a eof */',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278775.000034'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bcad67a2-9b1e-4474-a86b-2defef97bfce',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'for the ssh_connect() method, can you tell me what the int values are for SSH_OK, SSH_ERROR and SSH_AGAIN?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278737.000016'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e80bd035-40d1-42d1-8c78-ff14aa74777d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"The ssh_connect method doesn't seem to mention a username field or a password field. The function ssh_userauth_password may be appropriate:\\n\\nint ssh_userauth_password\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tusername,\\nconst char * \\tpassword \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nTry to authenticate by password.\\nThis authentication method is normally disabled on SSHv2 server. You should use keyboard-interactive mode.\\nThe 'password' value MUST be encoded UTF-8. It is up to the server how to interpret the password and validate it against the password database. However, if you read the password in some other encoding, you MUST convert the password to UTF-8.\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278576.000051'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b8f52325-c36a-4c3f-9b77-57246f455f1b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"for the ssh_connect() method, shouldn't I provide a username and password to connect to an ssh server?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278510.000038'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ea8e0c38-cc3a-4dd6-b99a-1fe070dcfc83',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'The only method I found involving \"localhost\" is ssh_options_getopt:\\n\\nint ssh_options_getopt\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nint * \\targcptr,\\nchar ** \\targv \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nParse command line arguments.\\nThis is a helper for your application to generate the appropriate options from the command line arguments.\\nThe argv array and argc value are changed so that the parsed arguments wont appear anymore in them.\\nThe single arguments (without switches) are not parsed. thus, myssh -l user localhost\\nThe command wont set the hostname value of options to localhost.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278444.000008'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c60d2dd1-1696-4f9d-8c04-8550b465e4d6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This looks like the best method to connect:\\n\\nint ssh_connect\\t(\\tssh_session session\\t)\\n\\nDescription \\nConnect to the ssh server.\\n\\nParameters \\nsession: The ssh session to connect.\\n\\nReturns \\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR on error. \\nSSH_AGAIN, if the session is in nonblocking mode, and call must be done again.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278408.000031'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'b5cf7b8f-ac61-47c9-b3af-a31885b778ab',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"how do I connect to localhost once I've created a new ssh_session?\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532278351.000072'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a348f48f-c9dd-4fe0-b114-8fedecdbd804',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This method returns an \"ssh_session\":\\n\\nReturns\\nA new ssh_session pointer, NULL on error.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532277865.000045'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '281af0de-1664-447d-a834-787599f6dec5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'is that a void method or does it return anything?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532277831.000048'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c6bfcebe-8002-4f34-940e-f5f31436e3a6',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Sure! It looks like the best way to create a new ssh session is with \\n\\nssh_session ssh_new\\t(\\tvoid \\t\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nCreate a new ssh session.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532277797.000035'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7668ea17-acf7-46c9-8353-bfe7bd6c742f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Hi Apiza, can you explain how to create a new ssh session?',\n",
       "     'user': 'UBW1N1YRL',\n",
       "     'ts': '1532277762.000030'},\n",
