       "   11: 0,\n",
       "   12: 0},\n",
       "  'entry': {0: '2-10', 1: '<2', 2: 'No', 3: '', 4: 'Intermediate'},\n",
       "  'exit': {0: 3, 1: 4, 2: 3, 3: 2, 4: 5, 5: 5, 6: 3, 7: 4, 8: 4},\n",
       "  'chatlog': {'ok': True,\n",
       "   'messages': [{'client_msg_id': 'b64bdf3c-5add-4281-80f5-a0d32f712151',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I couldn't find anything like that in the LibSSH documentation. Here is a web link that might help:\\n\\n<https://www.secureblackbox.com/kb/help/ref_err_sftperrorcodes.html>\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925892.000254',\n",
       "     'attachments': [{'title': 'SFTP Error Codes',\n",
       "       'title_link': 'https://www.secureblackbox.com/kb/help/ref_err_sftperrorcodes.html',\n",
       "       'text': 'SFTP Error Codes',\n",
       "       'fallback': 'SFTP Error Codes',\n",
       "       'from_url': 'https://www.secureblackbox.com/kb/help/ref_err_sftperrorcodes.html',\n",
       "       'service_icon': 'https://www.secureblackbox.com/favicon.ico',\n",
       "       'service_name': 'secureblackbox.com',\n",
       "       'id': 1,\n",
       "       'original_url': 'https://www.secureblackbox.com/kb/help/ref_err_sftperrorcodes.html'}]},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a871340a-2392-4172-8882-f25a1d05c8a8',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sftp error code',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925823.000274'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '9c6c468f-b788-470c-b3df-245affa9dd01',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"I couldn't find anything like that in the LibSSH documentation. Here is a web link that might help:\\n\\n<https://winscp.net/eng/docs/sftp_codes>\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925734.000266',\n",
       "     'attachments': [{'title': 'SFTP Status/Error Codes :: WinSCP',\n",
       "       'title_link': 'https://winscp.net/eng/docs/sftp_codes',\n",
       "       'text': 'Open source freeware SFTP, SCP and FTP client for Windows.',\n",
       "       'fallback': 'SFTP Status/Error Codes :: WinSCP',\n",
       "       'from_url': 'https://winscp.net/eng/docs/sftp_codes',\n",
       "       'service_icon': 'https://winscp.net/favicon.ico',\n",
       "       'service_name': 'winscp.net',\n",
       "       'id': 1,\n",
       "       'original_url': 'https://winscp.net/eng/docs/sftp_codes'}]},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c3d9ff0e-80b8-4679-8cd0-e90e0f89e799',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Server responses',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925661.000173'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '37c85f6a-1a01-4d48-836b-ccec3774d969',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is the documentation for `sftp_get_error`:\\n\\n```\\nint sftp_get_error\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nGet the last sftp error.\\nUse this function to get the latest error set by a posix like sftp function.\\n\\nParameters\\nsftp: The sftp session where the error is saved.\\n\\nReturns\\nThe saved error (see server responses), &lt; 0 if an error in the function occured.\\n\\nSee also\\nServer responses\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925620.000370'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a54025fc-cff9-47ad-8317-854552403cf1',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sftp get error',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925591.000241'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f23ea0dd-dd0f-4651-ac01-a1fa15b354bd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help write to the file:\\n\\n```\\nssize_t sftp_write\\t(\\tsftp_file \\tfile,\\nconst void * \\tbuf,\\nsize_t \\tcount \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nWrite to a file using an opened sftp file handle.\\n\\nParameters\\nfile: Open sftp file handle to write to.\\nbuf: Pointer to buffer to write data.\\ncount: Size of buffer in bytes.\\n\\nReturns\\nNumber of bytes written, &lt; 0 on error with ssh and sftp error set.\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_open()\\nsftp_read()\\nsftp_close()\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925110.000140'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8f9d3d94-d1f9-4d5e-a42a-a3c28da29881',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here is a function that might help create a new file:\\n\\n```\\nsftp_file sftp_open\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tfile,\\nint \\taccesstype,\\nmode_t \\tmode \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a file on the server.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The sftp session handle.\\nfile: The file to be opened.\\naccesstype: Is one of O_RDONLY, O_WRONLY or O_RDWR which request opening the file read-only,write-only or read/write. Acesss may also be bitwise-or'd with one or more of the following: O_CREAT - If the file does not exist it will be created. O_EXCL - When used with O_CREAT, if the file already exists it is an error and the open will fail. O_TRUNC - If the file already exists it will be truncated.\\nmode: Mode specifies the permissions to use if a new file is created. It is modified by the process's umask in the usual way: The permissions of the created file are (mode &amp; ~umask)\\n\\nReturns\\nA sftp file handle, NULL on error with ssh and sftp error set.\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_get_error()\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925082.000438'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'dd793d70-5784-4574-82a7-08acfcebf7fa',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here is a function that might help create a new directory:\\n\\n```\\nint sftp_mkdir\\t(\\tsftp_session \\tsftp,\\nconst char * \\tdirectory,\\nmode_t \\tmode \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nCreate a directory.\\n\\nParameters\\nsftp: The sftp session handle.\\ndirectory: The directory to create.\\nmode: Specifies the permissions to use. It is modified by the process's umask in the usual way: The permissions of the created file are (mode &amp; ~umask)\\n\\nReturns\\n0 on success, &lt; 0 on error with ssh and sftp error set.\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_get_error()\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925021.000339'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '1f89dc66-1a86-4e2d-b0a4-85d4819c5132',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Write to the file',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533925003.000489'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f3f99625-4146-4a11-ba9e-3dcbec1a0386',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help get a new sftp session:\\n\\n```\\nsftp_session sftp_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nStart a new sftp session.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA new sftp session or NULL on error.\\n\\nSee also\\nsftp_free()\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924990.000312'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '110c3ced-cf7e-4d13-ae6c-6b53eac3ee0a',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Create a new file',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924987.000102'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '325ed280-f0d1-463e-ac89-945b5bd01953',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Create a new directory',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924967.000441'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fbe7bc3a-326b-4dc1-bbc1-4a71d52412b5',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'new sftp_session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924950.000253'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '330454f8-c944-44d8-9208-22e938eae1ac',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here is a function that might help close the channel:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_close\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nClose a channel.\\nThis sends an end of file and then closes the channel. You won't be able to recover any data the server was going to send or was in buffers.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to close.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_free()\\nssh_channel_is_eof()\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924809.000358'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '94f6c40c-2de6-48e2-a76f-5f87bdcf1544',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'close channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924775.000410'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '7949a53e-55bc-4295-8bce-35d4aa78afeb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here is a function that might help send the eof:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_send_eof\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nSend an end of file on the channel.\\nThis doesn't close the channel. You may still read from it but not write.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to send the eof to.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred.\\nExample:\\n\\nrc = ssh_channel_send_eof(channel);\\nif (rc == SSH_ERROR) {\\n    return -1;\\n}\\nwhile(!ssh_channel_is_eof(channel)) {\\n    rc = ssh_channel_read(channel, buf, sizeof(buf), 0);\\n    if (rc == SSH_ERROR) {\\n        return -1;\\n    }\\n}\\nssh_channel_close(channel);\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_close()\\nssh_channel_free()\\nssh_channel_is_eof()\\n\\n\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924576.000224'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4c90fc43-4e1c-4c74-ba63-340e18dfbc35',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'sending the eof',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533924543.000137'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'e3c40bfe-484a-45c5-9c1c-dd005eb2778b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help get an error:\\n```\\nconst char* ssh_get_error\\t(\\tvoid * \\terror\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nRetrieve the error text message from the last error.\\n\\nParameters\\nerror: An ssh_session or ssh_bind.\\n\\nReturns\\nA static string describing the error.\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923553.000187'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '4c4af654-67ce-447a-9072-e60727040b52',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'get error from channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923513.000303'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'ee3d65b1-f2e9-4eb8-84a3-706d5a7c969b',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help get a new channel:\\n\\n```\\nssh_channel ssh_channel_new\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nAllocate a new channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nA pointer to a newly allocated channel, NULL on error.\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923321.000354'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'cea7901a-c834-4093-af58-f3e84d4f129f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help free the channel:\\n\\n```\\nvoid ssh_channel_free\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nClose and free a channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to free.\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923278.000293'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '080fd3f4-d279-4914-ba2e-514d752b8285',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help shut down the channel:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_scp_close\\t(\\tssh_scp \\tscp\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nClose the scp channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nscp: The scp context to close.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success or an SSH error code.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_scp_init()\\n\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923238.000357'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c2cba5f0-0369-4427-b6c2-7f6a605022fd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'new channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923183.000383'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'be378cb0-fdd5-4a3e-bf37-3f48332a3acc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help read a response:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_read\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nvoid * \\tdest,\\nuint32_t \\tcount,\\nint \\tis_stderr \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nReads data from a channel.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to read from.\\ndest: The destination buffer which will get the data.\\ncount: The count of bytes to be read.\\nis_stderr: A boolean value to mark reading from the stderr flow.\\n\\nReturns\\nThe number of bytes read, 0 on end of file or SSH_ERROR on error. In nonblocking mode it Can return 0 if no data is available or SSH_AGAIN.\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923167.000475'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'a1398bd3-3553-446d-84c5-971c7d5dc566',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Here is a function that might help execute a command:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_request_exec\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel,\\nconst char * \\tcmd \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nRun a shell command without an interactive shell.\\nThis is similar to \\'sh -c command\\'.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: The channel to execute the command.\\ncmd: The command to execute (e.g. \"ls ~/ -al | grep -i reports\").\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.\\nExample:\\n\\nrc = channel_request_exec(channel, \"ps aux\");\\nif (rc &gt; 0) {\\n    return -1;\\n}\\nwhile ((rc = channel_read(channel, buffer, sizeof(buffer), 0)) &gt; 0) {\\n    if (fwrite(buffer, 1, rc, stdout) != (unsigned int) rc) {\\n        return -1;\\n    }\\n}\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_request_shell()\\n\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923121.000367'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'bee6434a-4c43-4c83-88df-bdac5095cb15',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"There are lots of functions that might help open ssh_channel. Here's one:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_open_session\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen a session channel (suited for a shell, not TCP forwarding).\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: An allocated channel.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_open_forward()\\nssh_channel_request_env()\\nssh_channel_request_shell()\\nssh_channel_request_exec()\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923085.000179'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '8895ae82-e643-4cf9-bd81-5b750dfbe2bd',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'free the channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923075.000295'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '63427039-3655-43ef-9499-a0fcf2b4b322',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'shut down channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923072.000525'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '30aa6e36-2967-4a16-93e5-afad3697503d',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'read response from the channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923063.000170'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'af1eb924-6549-41e5-bb51-b299c983c782',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'Execute a command on the open channel.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533923040.000383'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '90d748a4-13b4-4d8c-8b7c-325de2eaee37',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'open ssh_channel',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922998.000015'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '393451fc-2d04-447e-8483-be9a9f71eb1c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function might help free the session:\\n\\n```\\nvoid ssh_free\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nDeallocate a SSH session handle.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The SSH session to free.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_disconnect()\\nssh_new()\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922654.000164'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'fe77759e-40cf-4ca5-abf2-e431eed48126',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'This function might help disconnect from the server:\\n\\n```\\nvoid ssh_disconnect\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nDisconnect from a session (client or server).\\nThe session can then be reused to open a new session.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The SSH session to use.\\n\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922632.000251'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '52539d71-140b-4fe5-94b3-a86583d91cbb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"This function might help authenticate the user:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_userauth_agent\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession,\\nconst char * \\tusername \\n)\\n\\nDescription\\nTry to do public key authentication with ssh agent.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The ssh session to use.\\nusername: The username, this SHOULD be NULL.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_AUTH_ERROR: A serious error happened.\\nSSH_AUTH_DENIED: The server doesn't accept that public key as an authentication token. Try another key or another method.\\nSSH_AUTH_PARTIAL: You've been partially authenticated, you still have to use another method.\\nSSH_AUTH_SUCCESS: The public key is accepted, you want now to use ssh_userauth_publickey().\\nSSH_AUTH_AGAIN: In nonblocking mode, you've got to call this again later.\\nNote\\nMost server implementations do not permit changing the username during authentication. The username should only be set with ssh_options_set() only before you connect to the server.\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922602.000217'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '0d5f6297-0994-4c68-833d-5749bd60496c',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'free the session',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922561.000077'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '65cc9f8b-c4d2-470b-88b8-e70766d6513f',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'disconnect from the server',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922556.000322'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c6c505eb-6a32-4659-9e71-4029655bbffc',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'authenticate the user to the server.',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922524.000397'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'c5929a11-4c9c-40e7-80c3-93cdd5fa79c2',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': \"Here is a function that might help check if the host is known:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_is_server_known\\t(\\tssh_session \\tsession\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nCheck if the server is known.\\nChecks the user's known host file for a previous connection to the current server.\\n\\nParameters\\nsession: The SSH session to use.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_SERVER_KNOWN_OK: The server is known and has not changed.\\nSSH_SERVER_KNOWN_CHANGED: The server key has changed. Either you are under attack or the administrator changed the key. You HAVE to warn the user about a possible attack.\\nSSH_SERVER_FOUND_OTHER: The server gave use a key of a type while we had an other type recorded. It is a possible attack.\\nSSH_SERVER_NOT_KNOWN: The server is unknown. User should confirm the MD5 is correct.\\nSSH_SERVER_FILE_NOT_FOUND: The known host file does not exist. The host is thus unknown. File will be created if host key is accepted.\\nSSH_SERVER_ERROR: Some error happened.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_get_pubkey_hash()\\nBug:\\nThere is no current way to remove or modify an entry into the known host table.\\n\\n\\n```\",\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922264.000298'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'd1d5bc07-f076-46ce-a9a1-a821e55d21fb',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'check that the host is known',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922184.000458'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': '6fc56abc-9898-4bd3-bb97-e5588e613c72',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'There are lots of functions that might be relevant. Here is one:\\n\\n```\\nint ssh_channel_open_auth_agent\\t(\\tssh_channel \\tchannel\\t)\\n\\nDescription\\nOpen an agent authentication forwarding channel.\\nThis type of channel can be opened by a server towards a client in order to provide SSH-Agent services to the server-side process. This channel can only be opened if the client claimed support by sending a channel request beforehand.\\n\\nParameters\\nchannel: An allocated channel.\\n\\nReturns\\nSSH_OK on success, SSH_ERROR if an error occurred, SSH_AGAIN if in nonblocking mode and call has to be done again.\\n\\nSee also\\nssh_channel_open_forward()\\n\\n\\n```',\n",
       "     'user': 'UB659D0FM',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922126.000172'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'dbd14e6a-48f1-4cdf-b49d-6c90b9114107',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
       "     'text': 'authetication',\n",
       "     'user': 'UC7SZ83KQ',\n",
       "     'ts': '1533922061.000257'},\n",
       "    {'client_msg_id': 'f94f452c-150b-4872-947c-3340ad5c5d08',\n",
       "     'type': 'message',\n",
